items.name: Horn Mask
items.item_description: The bleached satyr horn mounted atop this mask is said to allow the wearer to channel an ancestor's power.

items.name: Pangolin Shoulder Armor
items.item_description: Mastercrafted pauldrons of the Pangolin guild. They offer the strength of platemail at a fraction of the weight.

items.name: Ol' Snaggletooth
items.item_description: Witch Doctor found this stylish croc jaw discarded in the bush.

items.name: Grandfather's Ribs
items.item_description: Witch Doctor carries the ribs of his old grandfather, a shaman who held powerful magicks and spoke with influential spirits. Grandfather offers the Witch Doctor access to power in exchange for the opportunity to see blood spilled once more.

items.name: The Blood Chaser
items.item_description: A three section chained haft with double bladed axe head at the top. Nearly as dangerous to it's wielder as it is to the enemy.

items.name: Timestopper
items.item_description: If your ineffable transdimensional power over chronology fails to stop your enemy, try hitting them in the head with this sturdy mace.

items.name: Trolltooth Necklace
items.item_description: A carefully assembled collection of troll's teeth. Each tooth contains the trapped soul of its former owner.

items.name: Dragonclaw Hook
items.item_description: The claw from a black dragon's left toe. The only piece of the beast that survived an encounter with Pudge's voracious hunger.

items.name: Demon Blood Helm
items.item_description: A helm bearing the cyclopean visage of the Tarnsmen's demonic war god. It is said the Red Mist destroyed the god and took its symbols for their own.

items.name: Demon Blood Armor
items.item_description: Heavy platemail forged in the blood of the Tarnsmen's dead gods.

items.name: Demon Blood Guard
items.item_description: When the Red Mist consumed the Thousand Tarns, the lakes turned red with the blood of the slain. Many demons masquerading as the lawmakers and priests of that doomed civilization were also destroyed, their blood mixing with that of the mortals they once ruled.

items.name: Pegleg of the Cursed Pirate
items.item_description: A lost foot does not hinder Kunkka's desire for vengeance.

items.name: Three-Fold Mien of the Boar God
items.item_name: Three-Fold Mien of the Boar God
items.item_description: The aspect of the boar brings health, virility, and alacrity. The primal sign of four-seven-twelve.

items.name: Seven-Sealed the Fur Bracer
items.item_description: This is merely a bracer of fur. It has no particular aspect of interest and offers no magical protections. Still, it bears a great name and in so doing illustrates the hollowness of baseless pride.

items.name: Twelve-Tusks the Cape of Boars
items.item_description: Here we have Honor times twelve. As one might adorn a gloried warrior-king, each tusk a symbol of triumph.

items.name: Four-Fangs the Swordbreaker
items.item_description: The fangs of this fierce blade bite deep into your foe's bared weapon!

items.name: Pride of the Crew
items.item_description: Even the Captain must at times join his crew in the daily work aboard the ship.

items.name: Royal Admiral's Bicorne
items.item_description: A shipmaster's fine bicorne.

items.name: Tricorne of the Drowned
items.item_description: A well crafted tricorne edged in gold.

items.name: Wavecrester
items.item_description: A weathered, hooked harpoon and heirloom of Kunkka's line.

items.name: Battlefury
items.item_description: A weapon of timeless rage.

items.name: Berserker's Pauldron
items.item_description: "So many skulls to cleave. So many bodies to throw on the pile."

items.name: Berserker's Helm
items.item_description: "No business but war. No family but death. No mercy but the grave!"

items.name: Berserker's Belt
items.item_description: "Let the carnage begin."

items.name: Coat of the Elder Grove
items.item_description: A coat of leaves, common amongst the Druids of Verodicia, worn now by Nature's own prophet.

items.name: Horns of the Forest Lord
items.item_description: The avatar of Nature's Wrath may take whatever form he pleases. Choosing sometimes to appear as tree, other times as predator, or when it suits him as prey.

items.name: Toga of the Peace-Bringer
items.item_description: Quite relaxing.

items.name: Luxuriant Chin-Foliage
items.item_description: "Let those that would rule as Verdant Kings wear upon their brow horns sharpened with the wisdom of judgment and hang upon their chins a mighty symbol of their station."

items.name: Horns of Noblesse
items.item_description: A set of horns worthy of a king.

items.name: Cape of Verdant Dreaming
items.item_description: Wrapped in the power of the ancient woods.

items.name: Runestaff of Verodicia
items.item_description: The secret name of the woods-goddess shines from this holy staff.

items.name: Runed Ailettes
items.item_description: The runes inscribed upon these shoulders give the wearer the strength to carry the heaviest burden.

items.name: Lucky Tooth Necklace
items.item_description: A necklace of rare leviathan's teeth.

items.name: Captain's Hook
items.item_description: In waters as treacherous as those that surround the Trembling Isle, it is inevitable that even the most skilled captain sustain injury.

items.name: Tayrnhelm of the Swordmaster
items.item_description: The tall, serrated shafts along the side are said to improve hearing for the wearer.

items.name: Girth of the Swordmaster
items.item_description: Few would argue that keeping their thigh intact outweighs whatever discomfort this armor may cause.

items.name: Fluted Guard of the Swordmaster
items.item_description: The sheer size and weight of this piece were scoffed at until Sven used the shoulder spikes to impale an attacking ogre along the Feral Road.

items.name: Grip of the Swordmaster
items.item_description: Carefully constructed to guide a foe's blade away from the shoulder, or to catch it mid-swing.  Many have fallen overlooking such a simple piece of armor.

items.name: Meranth Executioner's Blade
items.item_description: A single edged blade perfect for quickly removing heads. Or legs. Or arms.

items.name: Taunt: Sniper's Celebration
items.item_description: Celebrate a sweet kill or a big play by showing your excitement to your enemy. He won't mind.

items.name: Rattlebite
items.item_description: Spirits are afraid of snakes, too.

items.name: Taunt: Beautiful Snowangel
items.item_description:
Crystal Maiden makes a snowangel!  You better believe it!
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: Playful Snowball
items.item_description: Crystal Maiden throws a snowball!

items.name: Taunt: Come and Get It!
items.item_description:
Axe requests more fools to slaughter!
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: Spider Shuffle
items.item_description:
Celebrate a critical push or an enemy team wipe with this spidery dance. 
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: Double-Headed Roar
items.item_description: Jakiro Roar Taunt

items.name: Taunt: Icemelter
items.item_description: Jakiro Icemelt Taunt

items.name: Dress of the Corpse Maiden
items.item_description: So often did Krobelus attempt to pass beyond the veil of death that those whose time had ended begged the chance with return her.

items.name: Taunt: Keep an Ear Out
items.item_description:
Did your enemy make a sound?
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Wuldastron the Twin-Blade of Giants
items.item_description: Few men could lift a blade so mighty.

items.name: Ultimate: Belly Flop
items.item_description: Gives Tidehunter a chance to belly flop when using his ultimate.

items.name: Attack: Fish Slap
items.item_description: Gives Tidehunter an alternate default attack animation.

items.name: Taunt: Celebration of Death
items.item_description:
Draw the eye of the ancestors upon your victory!
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: You!
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Taunt: Dive! Dive!
items.item_description: Periscope depth!

items.name: Taunt: Canonical Blast
items.item_description: That *is* his staff and he's excited to have killed you!

items.name: Taunt: Shredding the Lute Invisible
items.item_description:
Celebrate a critical push or an enemy team wipe by shredding some hot licks.
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: For Death and Honor
items.item_description:
Show your enemy your respect for their honorable deaths.
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: Face the Juggernaut
items.item_description: Invite your enemy to embrace their death in honorable combat.

items.name: Taunt: Tooting the Horn
items.item_description: Salute the death of your enemy.

items.name: Staff of the Tusk-Bereft
items.item_description: Let those who would sharpen their tusks on woodsy trunks take heed!

items.name: Tusked Bracers
items.item_description: Many would think the Nature's Prophet a thing of leaf and flower. They forget the rending claws of the forest bear and the tearing tusks of the deep woods boars.

items.name: Grand Crown of the Gigas
items.item_description: Is there any beast more majestic than the mighty Gigas? Even Alces and Cameloides bow before it.

items.name: Sinorian Sphere Staff
items.item_description: A Sinorian gemstone caps this staff, providing a magical focus for nature's incantations.

items.name: Taunt: Bo Staff Beckon
items.item_description: Nature's Prophet's Bo Staff Beckon

items.name: Taunt: Victory Jig
items.item_description:
Who knew he could dance?
	
	Equip the item and bind a key to the 'Taunt Item' button to use.

items.name: Taunt: Murder Lute
items.item_description: Verily Nature's Prophet sings unto thee:  DIE!

items.name: Twin Bull Adornment
items.item_description: Among the myriad creatures of Verodicia's domain, the zebu and the aurochs stand as the most prideful.

items.name: Pauldron of Al-Fusha
items.item_description: Al-Fusha was a great satyr general in service to Verodicia. It is said that he fell in battle and much of his wargear lost. Of it, this spiked and goddess-blessed pauldron remains.

items.name: Castor's Spaulder
items.item_description: The riverlands hero Castor Twin-Tusks challenged Verodicia's chosen prophet to an arcane duel. He lost.

items.name: Defender of the Ivory Isles
items.item_description: The Ivory Isles were lost with the theft of the Defender. Having slain the thieves, Juggernaut carries it with honor!

items.name: Visage of the Ivory Isles
items.item_description: Carved entirely from the ivory heart of the long extinct corodont.

items.name: Curled Root-Staff
items.item_description: This druidic root-staff symbolizes the Prophet's ability to bend the tree-men to his will.

items.name: Flared Wooden Crest
items.item_description: A simple, but decorative crest of wood. Designed to provide protection from the hated axe.

items.name: Fireborn Odachi
items.item_description: Forged in the fires that bubbled up from the sea on the night your homeland sank beneath the waves!

items.name: Taunt: Kata of Foot and Earth
items.item_name: Taunt: Kata of Foot and Earth
items.item_description: Demonstrate your martial skill with this kata.

items.name: Doubly Braided Beard
items.item_description: A force as mighty as nature itself should not be content with merely one beard.

items.name: Druidic Ritual Crest
items.item_description: Upon each plank is written a death-prayer to Verodicia and the name of an enemy of the deep forest.

items.name: Stoic Mask of the High Plains
items.item_name: Stoic Mask of the High Plains
items.item_description: The aspect of the high plains ram imbues its bearer with the endurance of mountains.

items.name: Wolf Cape of the High Plains
items.item_name: Wolf Cape of the High Plains
items.item_description: A warrior that slays the wolf with open handed strikes may bear its aspect into war as a symbol of courage and tenacity.

items.name: Aspect Wraps of the High Plains
items.item_name: Aspect Wraps of the High Plains
items.item_description: A set of serviceable bracers, made from the mighty mountain wolf.

items.name: Long-Fang the Grey Blade
items.item_description: "In the grip, the left hand must know Ardent Volition and the right hand must know Cultivated Grace. In this way the strike that follows bears both intentionality and respect. It is only the brute who strikes without these considerations."

items.name: Beard of Cycles
items.item_description: Does this beard represent the brutal cycle of life in the wild? Or is it tied back simply to prevent it from getting in the way of one's mayhem? Perhaps it holds both a symbol and a purpose.

items.name: Diadem of the Goddess Enthroned
items.item_description: Glory to her that brings the wind and upon it life's essence!

items.name: Drape of Foliate Magery
items.item_description: While lesser druids draw upon blood and mana to work their arts, Nature's Prophet taps directly the heart of Verodicia's wrathsome will.

items.name: Guard of the Deep Tribes
items.item_description: The men of the deep forest are not like their milk-fed cousins. Primal, driven by instinct and a will to survive, they call upon nature's pantheon and know nothing of gentle gods.

items.name: Pine-Sage Sigil Stones
items.item_description: Two sigils that bear the signs of an Elder Ecology.

items.name: Modestly Braided Beard
items.item_description: Even for the Avatars of Immortals modesty is sometimes called for.

items.name: Taunt: Kata of Blade and Sky
items.item_name: Taunt: Kata of Blade and Sky
items.item_description: The strike is not merely a tool to bring death. It is an expression of worth.

items.name: Cuffs of Oak and Yew
items.item_description: "Below me trees unnumber'd rise, beautiful in various dyes; the gloomy pine, the poplar blue, the yellow beech, the sable-yew, the slender fir, that taper grows, the sturdy oak with broad-spread boughs..."

items.name: Kraken Shell
items.item_description: The massive, shelled sea-krakens are considered both a delicacy, and a worthy foe.  Their shells are highly prized as both shelter and armor.

items.name: Octopus Hat
items.item_description: Is it trying to hitch a ride?  Is it trying to mate with his head?  Does it think it can influence the Tidehunter's thoughts?  Who knows!

items.name: Grand Claive of the Unshamed
items.item_description: "Ware the wanderer who walks with head held high, back unstooped, and arm held ready. The one that so boldly denies his disgrace has no such disgrace to deny! Surely that one is an assassin cloaked in contempt."

items.name: Wyrm Shield of Uldorak
items.item_description: The Dragon Knight bore this shield the day he fought and slew the Time Dragon Uldorak.

items.name: Belt o' Wicked Badness
items.item_description: The skulls of the Witch Doctor's tribal ancestors adorn this belt.

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Ice Axe
items.item_description: To brave the peaks beyond Icewrack requires tools specific to the job.

items.name: Kimono of the Ebony Tower
items.item_description: The greatest warrior stands between Ivory and Ebony, lending sword and hand but not heart or mind.

items.name: Bracers of the Ebony Tower
items.item_description: A lord so adorned will bend the will of many.

items.name: Relic Blade of the Kuur-Ishiminari
items.item_description: Many generations ago a great clan of stone workers crafted blades of jade such as this. While perhaps not as easy to wield or maintain as steel, the weapon nonetheless bears a grand nobility and a fine edge.

items.name: Kantusa the Script Sword
items.item_description: The sword is engraved in fine script telling the fated story of the one whose soul is sealed within.

items.name: Omnishred the Defiant
items.item_description: An artistic weapon, curved and elegant. When held within a powerfully gloved hand it burns with a desire to bring metal to mortal men!

items.name: Healing Ward of the Kuur-Ishiminari
items.item_description: The gargoyles and spirit-watchers of the Kuur-Ishiminari craft-clan bear witness to deeds both glorious and profane with never closing eyes of jade.

items.name: Call of the Dendrochron
items.item_description: This item changes the appearance of the treant warriors summoned by Nature's Call. Even the dreaded axe cannot hold their kind in check.

items.name: 100-Proof Jug
items.item_description: Courage may be born of a fearless demeanor or a masterful blade-arm. For those who lack these things, there is always the bottle and the jug.

items.name: Fine Bone Bracers
items.item_description: Bracers crafted from the fine bone of some alien beast.

items.name: Prey-Tracker's Aspect Mask
items.item_description: Juggernaut has faced many great demons and abominations. A few of these hunt with an alien intellect. He has crafted this mask to capture some aspect of their cunning and horror.

items.name: Staff of the Eagle
items.item_description: The prophet of Nature is not only a ward of the green things, but also of the myriad beasts and birds.

items.name: Blade of the Dark Ancients
items.item_description: The fragmented souls of tormented gods dwell within the blade's obsidian form.

items.name: Habit of the Seeker
items.item_description: The Flayed Ones cannot be destroyed nor can they be banished to some outer realm. Only through endless bloodshed can they be placated and their wrath stayed.

items.name: Hlotl-Feather Gloves
items.item_description: Adorned with the steel-like feathers of the Hlotl-beast, these gloves offer both protection and a benediction to Those That Ever-Thirst.

items.name: Hlotl-Tusk Headdress of the Seeker
items.item_description: Adorned in tusks of great beasts slain in the high peaks of Xhacatocatl, the priests of the Flayed Twins seek blood to keep their greedy gods appeased.

items.name: Hlotl-Feather Necklace
items.item_description: Among the shrouded reaches of Xhacatocatl hunt terrible beasts, fanged and feathered. It is after the fashion of these stalkers that the Bloodseeker has been molded.

items.name: Wyrm Helm of Uldorak
items.item_description: Many years before his fateful encounter with the Eldwurm, the Dragon Knight battled with and slew the Time-Dragon Uldorak. The much relieved and newly crowned King Tansis XIII ordered this helm forged as a gift and reward.

items.name: Wyrm Bracers of Uldorak
items.item_description: The Kings of Candoness suffered under the tyranny of the Time-Dragon Uldorak for many generations. For with each passing of the Candonite Crown, the dragon would appear demanding tribute in gold and magic trinkets.

items.name: Wyrm Skirt of Uldorak
items.item_description: Dowager Queen Tansis XII called upon a brave dragon slayer to ambush Uldorak upon her son's crowning day. Expecting no plots from the cowed people of Candoness, Uldorak was caught by surprise and slain.

items.name: Wyrm Pauldrons of Uldorak
items.item_description: Upon this pauldron the crest horns of the Time-Dragon Uldorak are mounted.

items.name: Gloves of the Admirable Admiral
items.item_description: Fine white gloves of silk. Noble clothing like this serves to set the Captain above his crew and to also motivate them with the promise of hard-earned wealth.

items.name: Ceremonial Rapier
items.item_description: More a prize than a weapon, this rapier was looted from some unfortunate prince's treasure ship as it navigated the Narrow Channel.

items.name: Sword of the Seventy-Seven Seas
items.item_description: Here we have a weapon truly worthy of a man such as Kunkka. Exotic and well-balanced, this cutlass cuts an image as smartly as it cuts a man.

items.name: Grand Curls of the Admirable Admiral
items.item_name: Grand Curls of the Admirable Admiral
items.item_description: Show them that you are a man of privledge.

items.name: Seafarer's Shoes
items.item_description: A fine pair of leather shoes with rubber soles, for when the Captain must work his charms on land.

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Parka
items.item_description: There is no better guard against the arctic cold than the pelt of an Icewrack wolf.

items.name: Light Cape of Sir Davion
items.item_description: The strength of a dragon knight lies not in his arm or sword, but in his heart.

items.name: Slayer-Sword of Sir Davion
items.item_description: When facing a dragon the edge of one's blade means less than the sharpness of one's mind.

items.name: Pauldrons of Sir Davion
items.item_description: A dragon knight is protected not by armor, but his faith.

items.name: Bracers of Sir Davion
items.item_description: Achieving mastery against dragons is impossible without first achieving mastery of the self.

items.name: Back-Ache
items.item_description: A rare but useful mutation.  The spikes are actually malformed teeth that grew out of place, and well out of hand.

items.name: Excavator's Treasure
items.item_description: The darkest deeps hold many extinct skulls.

items.name: Excavator's Decorated Treasure
items.item_description: The darkest deeps hold many extinct skulls.

items.name: Naval Mine
items.item_description: When it fell to the depths and smashed a favorite coral bed, the Tidehunter swore to reunite the device with its owner.

items.name: Swamp Fins
items.item_description: Nobody is certain whether this display means the Tidehunter is angry or in heat.  Either way, none have survived to ask.

items.name: Pillar of Strength
items.item_description: Axe cares nothing for the great castles and mighty holds of his enemies. He shatters their stanchions and crumbles their columns, transforming the rubble into weapons of war.

items.name: Stone Loins
items.item_description: A warrior as large as Axe rarely finds armor that fits. Often it is more practical to simply tie together bits of stone and metal.

items.name: Stone Guard
items.item_description: Armor crafted from the rubble of a conquered civilization.

items.name: Stone Helmet
items.item_description: A helm worn by the footmen of an empire crushed by Axe long ago.

items.name: Dragonbone Helm of Sir Davion
items.item_description: Successful dragon knights boast few scars. The ones that get hit rarely live long.

items.name: Helm of the Radiant Crusader
items.item_description: The inside is reinforced and padded to protect against heavy blows.

items.name: Armor of the Radiant Crusader
items.item_description: The added weight reminds the wearer of what he fights for, and the costs of failure.

items.name: Bracers of the Radiant Crusader
items.item_description: They are as pristine as the day they were made, but do not be fooled into thinking they have never seen combat.

items.name: Sigil of the Radiant Crusader
items.item_description: Those who don these fabrics must swear never to fall in battle, for it is considered a sin to defile such a garment with earth.

items.name: Hammer of the Radiant Crusader
items.item_description: Intended as an trophy for the most stalwart of the order's crusaders, the great smiths ensured it would be just as impressive above a hearth as it would be in combat.

items.name: Enameled Shield of Sir Davion
items.item_description: A dragon knight's shield is often more important than his sword. Dragons always strike first.

items.name: Champion of Emauracus
items.item_description: The wings symbolize the soaring heights of the cliffs of Emauracus, where it is said that the Omniscience itself may bless the pious with holy visions.

items.name: Raw Hide
items.item_description: Even the best swimmer may be caught unaware.

items.name: Cerebral Support
items.item_description: What ancient beast once wore this?  The Tidehunter cares not.

items.name: Skeletal Catch
items.item_description: There might still be a little meat on it.  But probably not.

items.name: Femur Thrasher
items.item_description: A sharp, cracked femur of some unidentifiable sea-beast.

items.name: Beast-Jaw Bludgeoner
items.item_description: A rather clumsy attempt at a weapon. The jaw of...something...has been lashed to a broken piece of mast.

items.name: Mask of the Freelancer
items.item_description: This old gladiatorial helm serves Sven well as he travels the land in search of honor and gold.

items.name: Shoulderguard of the Freelancer
items.item_description: Rogue swordmasters must balance the need for protection with the need for speed. This pauldron protects Sven's leading shoulder, but leaves his back arm unencumbered.

items.name: Pantaloons of the Freelancer
items.item_description: These fine pantaloons show that Sven's travels have led him into gold as much as glory.

items.name: Sword of the Freelancer
items.item_description: "Bitter the orphans journey--and lonely the orphan's grave."

items.name: Dragonmaw
items.item_description: Dragonmaw is mighty even among the Named Swords. It's jagged teeth rip at even the strongest hides, laying bear the vulnerable flesh beneath.

items.name: Pirate Slayer's Bracer
items.item_description: A gigantic bracer made from bits of sail and tied with line.

items.name: Pirate Slayer's Tricorn
items.item_description: Someone has taken the sail of a pirate ship and crudely sewn it into a mockery of a pirate's tricorn.

items.name: Bindings of the Rift
items.item_description: Envious of Dark Seer's pointed skull, Faceless Void channels the fabric of the Rift to focus not only his intellect, but his entire "head."

items.name: Squiddles
items.item_description: A rather oversized, stuffed squid plushie. He's cute and slimy and his name is Squiddles.

items.name: Spectrolite Staff
items.item_description: A staff bearing an array of spectrolite mana focusing crystals set in gold.

items.name: Sword of the Admirable Admiral
items.item_description: An exceptional specimen, surely the Captain's first pick of the loot. The hilt is dressed in worked gold and exotic stones. The blade blessed with a strangely glowing enchantment.

items.name: Executioner's Axe
items.item_description: A blood spattered and heavily notched blade. It has seen much use.

items.name: Executioner's Cape
items.item_description: A heavy woolen cloak dyed black. It could make even Axe seem stealthy.

items.name: Executioner's Trophies
items.item_description: Those who deny the strength of the Axe soon find a worthy place from which to witness his deeds.

items.name: Executioner's Hood
items.item_description: The work of the Axe is grim and endless.

items.name: Aspect Mask of Fulminant Rage
items.item_description: It is ever the warrior's charge to keep anger in check.  In the heat of battle, however, controlling emotions are the least of one's concerns.

items.name: Cold Case Bow
items.item_description: Twin-frost orbs charge this bow with arcane energy.

items.name: Twinblade of the Veil
items.item_description: The twinblade is designed to provide balance and flexibility in combat. The user can strike enemies quickly and at unexpected angles.

items.name: Rune Hammer
items.item_description: A solidly built hammer, inscribed with the names of the Holy Hierophants and imbued with the might of the Omniscience.

items.name: Shuriken of the Hidden Hunter
items.item_description: This shuriken's blades are clean and sharp, a weapon fresh and ready.

items.name: Harvester of the Hidden Hunter
items.item_description: A curved scythe, used to capture men or cut them down like so much wheat.

items.name: Cleaver of the Hidden Hunter
items.item_description: An already heavy blade, made even heavier by the weighted ring looped through the top. This is not a weapon for finesse, but for taking the enemy's head in a single strike.

items.name: Forgemaster's Apron
items.item_description: Written upon it a lost language are the words, "Kiss the axe."

items.name: Forgemaster's Armlet
items.item_description: An armlet scratched and scorched. It has shown heavy use at the forge.

items.name: Forgemaster's Hammer
items.item_description: The only day Axe declared defeat was the day he tried to forge a weapon with an axe.

items.name: Forgemaster's Mask
items.item_description: The warriors of the Red Mist are not only superb fighters, but also master smiths. Each grunt is expected to craft his own sword and his own shield. Should his war tools fail him on the battlefield, the grunt has only his own hands to blame.

items.name: Ice Burst Bow
items.item_description: A wicked bow bristling with crystalline spikes.

items.name: The Cleaver of Might
items.item_description: Heaviest at its furthest tip, the cleaver is said to be able to cut through anything, be it steel or stone or bone.

items.name: Hardened Hunter's Bracer
items.item_description: One might think that the bounty hunter thinks nothing of his victim. On the contrary, the bounty hunter understands his target's pain and fear. He simply does not care.

items.name: Hardened Hunter's Armor
items.item_description: The value of a contract is measured not only in the bounty paid, but in the loot taken from the mark's cold corpse.

items.name: Nature's Shortbow
items.item_description: Short in size, but long on killing power, this little bow is an ideal weapon for dispatching overconfident enemies.

items.name: Chronite Armor
items.item_description: The time-altering properties of chronite stabilizes the Faceless Void's presence in the material realm.

items.name: Chronite Bracers
items.item_description: A pair of chronite encrusted bracers that seem to warn the Faceless Void of his enemies' future attacks.

items.name: Chronite Scepter
items.item_description: A symbol of power within the infinite halls of Claszureme.

items.name: Voidkeeper's Visage
items.item_description: The Faceless Void has known many forms, his body twisted by the nameless forces that whorl and eddy within the time streams.

items.name: Ice Burst Bracers
items.item_description: Despite their size, these sharp ice-like crystals weigh almost nothing and so do not hinder the Drow Ranger's use of the bow.

items.name: Ice Burst Greaves
items.item_description: Light plate greaves decorated with sharp crystal spikes. These are designed to provide protection without inhibiting movement.

items.name: Creeper's Cruel Painsaw
items.item_description: None would say that Gondar the Bounty Hunter does not take pleasure in his work.

items.name: Creeper's Cruel Hook
items.item_description: Gold is only one reason why Gondar hunts.

items.name: Creeper's Cruel Shuriken
items.item_description: 'Ouch!'

items.name: Wicked Collar of the Corpse Maiden
items.item_name: Wicked Collar of the Corpse Maiden
items.item_description: The petrified remnants of ancient souls still cling to Krobelus in a futile attempt to return to life.

items.name: Ghastly Scarf of the Corpse Maiden
items.item_name: Ghastly Scarf of the Corpse Maiden
items.item_description: Returning from death, Krobelus often found wisps and remnants of desperate souls clinging to her shoulders.

items.name: Trident of the Sea Stalker
items.item_description: A trident cursed by a host of sea gods and sealed within in the depths of the Coral Breach for thousands of years.

items.name: Spiral Staff
items.item_description: A crystalline focus hung at the center of the staff gives the Witch Doctor unnatural sight.

items.name: Pincher Bow
items.item_description: A heavy bow of Pincher Iron, mined by the Drow deep beneath the earth.

items.name: Hardened Hunter's Mask
items.item_description: It's not uncommon for bandits to wear leather gorgets to protect their throats from the knives of their 'allies.'

items.name: Dressed Pauldron of the Mono Militis
items.item_name: Dressed Pauldron of the Mono Militis
items.item_description: This pauldron bears the cats-eye sigil of the Mono Militis sect and has been dressed with fine trim to show the elevated status of its owner.

items.name: Cyclopean Helm of the Mono Militis
items.item_name: Cyclopean Helm of the Mono Militis
items.item_description: A helm of the Mono Militis, its protective design occludes the wearer's natural sight. The forward mounted cats-eye gemstone is imbued with scrying magics that enhance the vision of the wearer.

items.name: Sword of the Mono Militis
items.item_description: The Mono Militis are one of several sects among the Vigil Knights. Adherents have tasked themselves with hunting down those who have strayed from the teachings of the Vigil Codex.

items.name: Sword of the Flameguard
items.item_description: A heavily weighted sword fashioned in the two-handed style of the Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights.

items.name: Pirate Slayer's Cutlass
items.item_description: The skull of an unfortunate sea captain adorns this rusty blade.

items.name: Pirate Slayer's Black Flag
items.item_description: The remains of a once terrible icon, now a symbol of the Tidehunter's power.

items.name: Horns of the Bone Scryer
items.item_description: "I scry with my little eye...a fabulous piece of headgear!"

items.name: War Blade
items.item_description: An exceptionally sharp war-blade.

items.name: War Blade - Off-Hand
items.item_description: An exceptionally sharp war-blade.

items.name: Kingslayer Axe
items.item_description: An axe crafted by four master smiths, each edge carefully wrought.

items.name: Helm of the Flameguard
items.item_description: The Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights are sworn to protect the ever-burning Holy Flame. While few in number, they are unmatched in swordsmanship.

items.name: Dressed Pauldron of the Flameguard
items.item_description: Flameguard armor is functional, but also highly ornate. From their stations among the Inner Colonnade the Flameguard make their watch over the Holy Flame.

items.name: Cape of the Flameguard
items.item_description: The Flameguard wear capes as blue as the Holy Flame they are sworn to protect. On the back is their sigil: a circle representing the Inner Colannade with an inscribed triangle symbolizing the Flame itself.

items.name: Skirt of the Flameguard
items.item_description: Beyond reproach and unwavering in their devotion, the Flameguard stand as living avatars of Knightly Duty.

items.name: Commander's Helm of the Flameguard
items.item_description: The Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights are sworn to protect the ever-burning Holy Flame. While few in number, they are unmatched in swordsmanship.

items.name: Commander's Gauntlet of the Flameguard
items.item_description: An armored gauntlet of the Flameguard sect, worn by that faction's gloried commanders.

items.name: Lucky Alpine Stalker's Hat
items.item_description: A well worn hat adorned with a lucky feather and several blessed cholgar-teeth.

items.name: Alpine Stalker's Scarf
items.item_description: To the north of Ulfsaar's home-wood lies a nameless stretch of jagged, frozen peaks. On occaision the ursine people must range these mountains, culling the wild mountain beasts lest they grow and threaten the sleeping cubs.

items.name: Alpine Stalker's Pants
items.item_description: Lightweight pants designed to preserve the wearer's agility more than his hide.

items.name: Alpine Stalker's Gloves
items.item_description: Wraps to keep a bear's paws warm, but claws free to rend and hew.

items.name: Back Hook
items.item_description: A cruelly twisted hook. Perfect for draining blood from an unexpecting victim.

items.name: Back Hook - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A cruelly twisted hook. Perfect for draining blood from an unexpecting victim.

items.name: Vile Carnival Hat
items.item_description: When life is cheap, souls are currency.

items.name: Dreaded Dreads
items.item_description: The braided nature of this hairstyle is said to symbolize one's tightly woven link to the ancestors.

items.name: Juju o' Wicked Badness
items.item_description: A carefully crafted soul-trap, adorned with the skull of a previous victim.

items.name: Staff o' Wicked Badness
items.item_description: The life essence of a sacrificial totem beast imbues this ritual staff.

items.name: Mask o' Wicked Badness
items.item_description: A mask crafted from the polished bones of a cruel Prefecturan noble. The Witch Doctor wears this mask when he wants influential spirits to take notice of his work.

items.name: Shrunken Head Staff
items.item_description: The head of Witch Doctor's mother hangs from this staff. Such a loving son.

items.name: Wooden Fetish Mask
items.item_description: It's supposed to be smiling.

items.name: Tribal Totem Mask
items.item_description: Not all of the Witch Doctor's enslaved spirits are ancestors. This household totem contains the trapped soul of a swamp dwelling Yando beast.

items.name: Flower Staff of the Peace-Bringer
items.item_description: A Candral-Flower plucked from the heart of the Endless Copse.

items.name: Lei of the Peace-Bringer
items.item_description: Hung about the neck and worn during festive events, the garland is a universal symbol of friendship, peace, and good tidings.

items.name: Horns of the Peace-Bringer
items.item_description: Horns curved into a sigil of peace.

items.name: Beard of the Peace-Bringer
items.item_description: Light and fluffy.

items.name: Pangolin Carapace
items.item_description: This shelled carapace armor is meant to offer both protection and camouflage.

items.name: Pangolin Scarf
items.item_description: A bright scarf marked with the sigil of the Pangolin hunters' guild.

items.name: Frost Spikes FIXUP BUNDLE
items.item_description: Use this bundle to unpack the Frost Spikes and Ice Burst Cloak items. These were previously one item, but have been broken into two.

items.name: Cape of the Burning Cabal
items.item_description: The invokers of the Burning Cabal favor Exort over all other disciplines.

items.name: Bracers of the Burning Cabal
items.item_description: Manipulation of the fire elements requires a delicate touch, lest the sorcerer burn. This pair of bracers have been imbued with minor fire protection enchantments.

items.name: Crest of the Burning Cabal
items.item_description: The war-crest of the Burning Cabal. This identifies the invoker as a specialist in fire manipulation.

items.name: Stylish Wizard's Topnot
items.item_description: Few wizards can be considered to be stylish, but the Invoker is not like other wizards.

items.name: Commander's Pauldron of the Flameguard
items.item_description: Flameguard armor is functional, but also highly ornate. From their stations among the Inner Colonnade the Flameguard make their watch over the Holy Flame. This variation is the armor of a Flameguard commander.

items.name: Commander's Cape of the Flameguard
items.item_description: The Flameguard wear capes as blue as the Holy Flame they are sworn to protect. On the back is their sigil: a circle representing the Inner Colannade with an inscribed triangle symbolizing the Flame itself. This variation is the armor of a Flameguard commander.

items.name: Commander's Skirt of the Flameguard
items.item_description: Beyond reproach and unwavering in their devotion, the Flameguard stand as living avatars of Knightly Duty. This variation is the armor of a Flameguard commander.

items.name: Demon Skull Staff
items.item_description: Witch Doctor clearly has a thing for skulls.

items.name: Staff of the Old Doctor
items.item_description: When the Witch Doctor rose to his position of power over his tribe, he fashioned this staff from the remains of the old Doctor. Perhaps it was meant as an honor, but most saw it as a warning.

items.name: Manifold Spear
items.item_description: A spear with three edges. It seems to reflect the light strangely.

items.name: Cape of Arcane Artistry
items.item_description: An archmagister must be the greatest at all things magical: spell-casting, scroll-reading, and costume-wearing.

items.name: Edgebearer's Helm
items.item_description: A helm as sharp as an axe.

items.name: Ringblade
items.item_description: The unusual edge of the Ringblade represents unending courage.

items.name: Hammer of Holy Words
items.item_description: A nameless weapon, wrapped in holy scripture taken from the Book of the All Seeing.

items.name: Death Mask of the Brave
items.item_description: In the face of the great beast, Juggernaut saw bravery.  In the mask made from the creature's skull, Juggernaut's foes see death.

items.name: Elder Tusk of the Brave
items.item_description: So honored was Juggernaut by the death of the great beast, that he wears its tusk as a memento of their battle.

items.name: Bone Bracer of the Brave
items.item_description: The great beast that gave the bone to make these bracers did not do so willingly, or without struggle.

items.name: No-Guard the Courageous Edge
items.item_description: To wield a blade without a guard is to commit one's self to perfecting the art of combat.  Make but a single mistake, the slightest miscalculation, and life becomes forfeit.

items.name: Sacral Apparel
items.item_description: The shrunken skull of the warrior who killed the first Tale-Teller has found a special place of honor with all Tellers since.

items.name: Drum of Tales
items.item_description: Every generation has a seer to act as chronicler and teller of old tales.  As each one dies, a small handful of their bones are preserved and placed in the drum so that their spirit might infuse the telling of old tales.  Though the drum itself has been replaced many times, the oldest bones within are hundreds of years old.

items.name: Mantle of Mysteries
items.item_description: None know whose bones line mantle's fringe.  Every teller must ask unanswerable questions.

items.name: Veil of Fables
items.item_description: The rich stories of the tribe are considered too sacred to be seen spoken by a mortal mouth.

items.name: Eul's Scepter of Divinity
items.item_description: With the right wind behind it, even the Blueheart Glacier itself can be made to travel.

items.name: Hammer Time
items.item_description: The shark said it couldn't be touched. Tidehunter disagreed.

items.name: Deathwielder
items.item_description: The Veiled Sisters pride themselves on having blades that can pierce anything.

items.name: Wheel of Fortitude
items.item_description: Little else remains of Kunkka's helmsman.

items.name: Ancient Mask of Intimidation
items.item_description: Many wonder what horrors inspired the shape of this mask.  Some believe it shows the back of some long-forgotten subterranean creature.  Others say it is the face of a demon.  Only Juggernaut knows for sure.

items.name: Radiant Crystal Bracer
items.item_description: Bracers that infuse the living waters with Radiant essence. When fighting for the Dire, Morphling wears them with purely ironic intent.

items.name: Radiant Crystal Crown
items.item_description: The promise of a Radiant crown was enough to draw from its path the frozen comet in which Morphling waited to take watery form.

items.name: Radiant Crystal Pauldrons
items.item_description: Plucked from the deeps of a still mountain pool, it was as if these pauldrons had waited an eternity to be discovered by the one fated to wear them.

items.name: Radiant Crystal Crests
items.item_description: Morphling's terrifying charge is made all the more intimidating when he bristles with these stunning Radiant crests.

items.name: Timebreaker
items.item_description: While a stopped clock may be right on occasion, savage deployment of the Timebreaker is always appropriate.

items.name: Grand Blade of the Demigod
items.item_description: The name of the ancient kingdom that fell to this terrible blade has long been forgotten to history.  The blade itself, however, seems impossible to lose track of.

items.name: Armor of the Purist Champion
items.item_description: Omniknight wears such armaments proudly.

items.name: Bracer of the Purist Champion
items.item_description: Omniknight wears his feelings on his sleeve.  That and a blue bracer, which he'll use to smite his enemies in the name of the Omnicient.

items.name: Hammer of the Purist Champion
items.item_description: When your best tool is a hammer, the world (and the head of the heretic) begins to look like a nail.

items.name: Circlet of the Purist Champion
items.item_description: For Omniknight, no show of loyalty is too great.

items.name: Force Staff
items.item_description: Sometimes a little push is all you need.

items.name: Exquisite Doubled Axe of the Veil
items.item_name: Exquisite Doubled Axe of the Veil
items.item_description: Occasionally a target will be well-armored against more conventional blades.  Or they may be hiding behind a large door.

items.name: Ice Crystal Bow
items.item_description: Wielding a bow made of ice requires a delicate hand, and a backup plan.

items.name: Shuriken of the Reaper
items.item_description: A shuriken made to be deadly regardless of how it makes contact.

items.name: Bladed-Staff of the Reaper
items.item_description: Good for crops.  Great for heads.

items.name: Makeshift Sword of the Reaper
items.item_description: A blade need not be made for combat to be useful in war.

items.name: Qaldin Assassin's Dagger
items.item_description: Few hunters ever make contact with a Qaldin Assassin.  Fewer still are able to commission a blade from them.

items.name: Qaldin Assassin's Slicer
items.item_description: Owning the weapon of a Qaldin Assassin is a mark of success that few hunters ever achieve.

items.name: Qaldin Assassin's Glaive
items.item_description: Perfectly balanced and unbelievably sharp, the weapons of a Qaldin Assassin are considered a luxury among those who kill for their living.

items.name: Helm of Claszureme
items.item_description: The runes upon the brow give vision beyond the flow of time.

items.name: Sylnashar the Winged Axe
items.item_description: Lost for centuries, the winged axe known as Sylnashar was once the favored weapon of an ancient king.

items.name: Shoulders of the Slain Dragon
items.item_description: Not the actual shoulders of a dragon, but a skilled artist's rendition of it.

items.name: Elemental Ice Infusion
items.item_description: Infused with the strength of glacial ice, Tiny has the power to scour his enemies from the battlefield.

items.name: Bloodmist Belt
items.item_description: With the Army of Red Mist now a bloody heap, the Bloodmist Army rises to fill the void.

items.name: Bloodmist Helm
items.item_description: This helm sits heavily on the head to strengthen the neck below.

items.name: Bloodmist Crescent Axe
items.item_description: Where the Army of Red Mist trained to aim for the neck, the Bloodmist prefer to aim for the belly.

items.name: Bloodmist Pauldrons
items.item_description: These pauldrons were once owned by a mighty officer of the Bloodmist Army.  Axe is only too pleased to tell the tale of their encounter.

items.name: Demon Claive
items.item_description: Sven seemed overcome with nostalgia at the sight of this sword, though he would not say why.

items.name: Weighted Claive
items.item_description: What it may lack in weight, it makes up for in finesse.

items.name: Bracers of Profound Perfection
items.item_description: While many wizards are jealous of the Invoker's unimaginable power, others are merely jealous of his peerless taste.

items.name: Crest of the Magus Magnus
items.item_description: A crest that crackles with the arcane might of Wex.

items.name: Hood of Endless Intellect
items.item_description: The Invoker has little need for this hood's magical intellect boosting enchantments. He is already far more intelligent than you could possibly ever comprehend.

items.name: Iron Bear's Belt
items.item_description: It is rare to find such a useful relic from the Tribal Wars still intact.

items.name: Iron Bear's Plates
items.item_description: During the Tribal Wars, the etching on the shoulders was used to mark one's homeland and clan should the wearer fall in battle.

items.name: Iron Bear's Cutter
items.item_description: Until the Tribal Wars, the Ursa clan never thought to cover themselves in armor.  With the war now a distant memory, such arms are now considered more ceremonial than practical.

items.name: Iron Bear's Skullcap
items.item_description: A relic of the Tribal Wars, this cap is said to have belonged to a powerful chieftain.

items.name: Shoulders of the Comet's Tail
items.item_description: The stars themselves travel the skies in search of illumination.

items.name: Ruling Sword
items.item_description: It is said that to hold the Ruling Sword is to conquer one's destiny.

items.name: Metal Horns
items.item_description: In a time long forgotten, a grateful king once gifted the Prophet these horns as thanks for aid of the forest.

items.name: Obsidian Blade Bracers
items.item_description: Such lethal pieces have no place outside the field of battle, which is why Huskar rarely takes them off.

items.name: Obsidian Blade Warhelm
items.item_description: The heat of volcanic forces, condensed and cooled, focused into a point, is a powerful symbol of Huskar's warrior nature.

items.name: Obsidian Blade Pauldron
items.item_description: They say that lava, as it cools, dreams its final form. It's as if this obsidian in its infancy knew of Huskar's coming.

items.name: Spiked Bracers of the Ravager
items.item_description: To kill a ravager is a sacred rite for the ursa, and every piece of the carcass must be put to use.

items.name: Sash of the Ravager
items.item_description: Made from the smooth belly of an otherwise spiny ravager.

items.name: Skull of the Ravager
items.item_description: Only the fiercest hunter may lay claim to the skull of a spiked ravager.

items.name: Quills of the Ravager
items.item_description: The quills of a ravager are threaded throughout the fur to create a trap for any would-be predator.

items.name: Master Assassin's Shuriken
items.item_description: The blade end and grip are carefully balanced to sail through the air accurately, and with ease.

items.name: Master Assassin's Tails
items.item_description: The trailing cloth obscures the assassin's form and, in a pinch, can be used to thwart enemy blades.

items.name: Master Assassin's Shoulders
items.item_description: Built to deflect enemy weapons, the shoulder plates are carefully tailored to the wearer.

items.name: Master Assassin's Mask
items.item_description: The cloth is treated with oils and wax to stave off enemy poisons.

items.name: Master Assassin's Mancatcher
items.item_description: Designed to catch and hold the target, no matter which point is used.

items.name: Master Assassin's Grim Cutter
items.item_description: The forked tip allows the wielder to pry back any armor the target may be wearing.

items.name: Reaver
items.item_description: Forged in volcanic fire, bathed in the blood of countless foes, the Reaver is a weapon that has never known mercy.

items.name: Trap Jaw
items.item_description: There is more to catching prey than merely stalking them through the woods.

items.name: Hood of the Hierophant
items.item_description: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always approach with head bowed.

items.name: Chestplate of the Hierophant
items.item_description: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always sense the power that protects him.

items.name: Heavy Pauldrons of the Hierophant
items.item_description: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always feel the weight of responsibility upon his shoulders.

items.name: Holy Words of the Hierophant
items.item_description: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always heed the words of his order.

items.name: Bracers of the Hierophant
items.item_description: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always guard against any threat.

items.name: Nightmare Blade
items.item_description: Belched up from the hells beyond, the cursed Nightmare Blade is not of the mortal plane.  Whosoever dares to swing the sword in combat will find their dreams haunted by all whom the blade has cut down.

items.name: Bloodletter
items.item_description: A ceremonial blade, used to prepare sacrifice to the Flayed Ones.

items.name: Bloodletter - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A ceremonial blade, used to prepare sacrifice to the Flayed Ones.

items.name: Glaive of the Mage Slayer - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Glaive of the Mage Slayer - Off-Hand
items.item_description: Brutality defined many of the early weapons used by the Anti-Mage.

items.name: Helm of the Slain Dragon
items.item_description: A cage of gold for your knight's gilded head.

items.name: Hammer of Hope
items.item_description: For hope is brought to all who witness the hammer's fall and repent.

items.name: Shard of the Rift
items.item_description: At the border between the realms lie stones that exist outside of time itself.  To be struck with such a stone is to feel an eternity of pain.

items.name: Blade of Dead Kings
items.item_description: Ostarion's servants presented him with this sword.  The bones of fallen kings form the grip and hilt, while the blade is forged from the armor in which they died.

items.name: Bonehunter Bracers
items.item_description: To the west lie the drylands, where the Bonehunters stalk.  Their tribute to the Flayed Ones is small, but their ferocity is unmatched.

items.name: Bonehunter Tuskguard
items.item_description: It is tradition that a Bonehunter adorns himself with the teeth of their fiercest kill.

items.name: Bonehunter Belt
items.item_description: The crimson pattern which covers this garment must be regularly restored with fresh blood.

items.name: Bonehunter Skullguard
items.item_description: The beasts that wander the drylands are fierce, but no few are match for the Bonehunters.

items.name: Bonehunter Slicer
items.item_description: The Bonehunters adhere to the ways of a time before weapons could be forged from steel.

items.name: Bonehunter Slicer - Off-Hand
items.item_description: The Bonehunters adhere to the ways of a time before weapons could be forged from steel.

items.name: Bonehunter Spineguard
items.item_description: The Bonehunters believe that if it is good enough to protect from within, then it must also be good enough to protect from without.

items.name: Epoch
items.item_description: The cudgel of the ageless, said to be the result of a millennia of craftsmanship compressed to the blink of an eye.

items.name: Helm of a Savage Age
items.item_description: A ceremonial headgarb to honor the ferocity of a savage age.

items.name: Armor of a Savage Age
items.item_description: In a savage age, before the Ursa earned the gift of speech, they communicated alliances and homelands through elaborately designed patterns and sigils.

items.name: Bracer of a Savage Age
items.item_description: In hallowed ceremony on honored days, the Ursa remember a savage time before they earned the gift of speech.

items.name: Belt of a Savage Age
items.item_description: A ceremonial covering honoring a savage time before the Ursa earned the gift of speech.

items.name: Funereal Dress of the Bone Scryer
items.item_name: Funereal Dress of the Bone Scryer
items.item_description: Far-seeing prophets who see anything other than Death are merely fooling themselves. Death Prophet knows how every occasion ends, and thus her attire is always appropriate.

items.name: Scarf of the Bone Scryer
items.item_description: When visions of Death bring a chill, this scarf keeps Death Prophet warm. Then again, she enjoys a little chill.

items.name: Head-Ache
items.item_description: A rare but useful mutation. The spikes are actually malformed teeth that grew out of place, and well out of hand.

items.name: Rhuis Tuning-Fork
items.item_description: A skilled warrior wielding this sword can tell the type of blade he faces by the sound it makes when they clash.

items.name: Carved Grin of the Trickster
items.item_description: But does Yurnero ever smile beneath the mask?

items.name: Riftshadow Roamer's Pluckin' Fiddle
items.item_description: With five Meepos you've got quite the band.

items.name: Legion's Wrath
items.item_description: In the hands of one, the uses of this lance are few.  In the hands of many, however...

items.name: Dero's Staff of Sanity
items.item_description: To grip such a weapon is to maintain one's hold on reality.

items.name: Berserker's Witchslayer
items.item_description: The runes along the edge prevent it from being enchanted by those that may seek to disarm the wielder.

items.name: Crown of the Comet's Tail
items.item_description: Although unknown to the land-based historians of terrestrial empires, the mythologies of sea-dwelling creatures oft look to the moon and stars for wisdom and guidance.

items.name: The Spiritual Spirits
items.item_description: Among the Brewmasters of Oyo diligent drunkenness is the only path to enlightenment.

items.name: Flail of the Great Elder
items.item_description: The title of Brewmaster is won in combat. This ancient weapon is also passed with the title.

items.name: Crescent Sickle of the Druid
items.item_description: This sickle is a symbol and ritualistic tool of the Bear Clan, a forgotten druidic order that sought to restore the world.

items.name: Poor Armor of the Druid
items.item_description: The druids of the Bear Clan were outcasts to society, simple nature dwellers and forest walkers. They had little coin or use for coin.

items.name: Shoulder of the Noble
items.item_description: Each nobleblood general of the Royal House of Ambry bore these pauldrons as a part of their formal wear.

items.name: Sange and Yasha
items.item_description: A pair of magical short blades, balanced and light. Unpack this bundle to receive both Sange and Yasha for Riki.

items.name: Spine Sword
items.item_description: Most see being stabbed in the back as a hindrance, but for a few, it's an inspiration.

items.name: Vice of the West
items.item_description: Ugh.  It tastes like sour grapes.

items.name: Mask of the Many-Sighted
items.item_description: On the Isle of Masks, death is said to have many watchful eyes.

items.name: Lucky Belly Belt
items.item_description: Aggron says they found it just lying by the side of the road on a bandit they killed.

items.name: Champion's Belly Belt
items.item_description: Aggron says they won it in a game of chance.  Who are we to argue?

items.name: Golden Walrus Whacker
items.item_description: If you ask Aggron, they won it in a dice game.  If you ask its former owner, you'll get the silence of the grave.

items.name: Cloak of the Dawn
items.item_description: The Bear Clan taught that every rising sun was a gift, and so appointed one among them to greet the dawn each day.

items.name: Shoulders of the Twelfth Day
items.item_description: In the custom of the Bear Clan, each warrior must carry his newborn in a satchel on his shoulder for eleven full days to prove his strength.  On the twelfth day, armor is bestowed.

items.name: Recluse Reef Denizen
items.item_description: Recluse Reef is known for treacherous currents, lacerating corals, and barnacles big enough to drag down a galleon. In these evil waters, one denizen glides without fear, the undisputed master of Recluse Reef. Or anyway he glided...until Tidehunter needed a flail.

items.name: Wyvernguard Edge
items.item_description: No mere woodcutter's hatchet, the Wyvernguard Edge is a great-axe with the bite of a dragon.  Forged from the knights' steel found fused and glowing in the molten guts of a dozen slaughtered Pyrexae, the blade of Wyvernguard penetrates to the bleeding heart of any battle.

items.name: Bow of the Howling Wind
items.item_description: In the endless chill of the far north, it is said that the cold of death comes on a howling wind brought by a great white wolf.  Many a hunter has attempted to slay this grave spirit.  Yet in all the known histories, the stories record only one bow that has ever fired strong enough, and true enough, to pierce its side.

items.name: Ice Burst Cloak
items.item_description: A cloak of scintillating frost.

items.name: Frost Spikes
items.item_description: A playful crop of spikes that says 'I'm killing you and having fun doing it.' Includes a frost-tinged cloak to complete the image.

items.name: Salvaged Sword and Board
items.item_description: Sometimes you have to go with what you can find.

items.name: Direstone Crests
items.item_description: As the wave of Morphling crests, surging into battle, these Direstone crests come along for the ride.

items.name: Vambraces of the Slain Dragon
items.item_description: Forged from the finest dragon's gold, these vambraces are a bargain at any price.

items.name: Corpsemaker
items.item_description: While the edge has cracked and chipped on the lives of hundreds, it has never failed to finish the job.

items.name: Headhunter
items.item_description: This weapon once adorned a nobleman's mantel collecting dust, which is exactly the fate Axe made for the nobleman's head.

items.name: Direstone Bracers
items.item_description: Direstone is not a substance to be worn lightly. When Morphling dons these bracers, he means business.

items.name: Skeletal Claw of the Vandal
items.item_description: Lacking flesh, Clinkz adorns his skeletal hand with the claw of the Vandal.  Forged by smeevils in ages long past, this iron claw is for many hapless victims the iron grip of death itself.

items.name: Sacrificial Shortblade
items.item_description: If it was good enough to cut the heart from a heretic, then it is good enough to cut the heart from anyone.

items.name: Saberhorn's Helm
items.item_description: The helm of the legendary general Saberhorn has seen countless battles and wars.

items.name: Lash of the Summoned Lord
items.item_description: Izhai icha ensh safras!

items.name: Runic Bow of Corruption
items.item_description: A bow of bone and steel, emblazoned with archaic runes that corrupt all who can read their inscription.  Luckily, no one can.

items.name: Sigil of the Summoned Lord
items.item_description: Hollom tak vo'Ozh hedoq!

items.name: Plate of the Summoned Lord
items.item_description: Ozh icha gluth ahm'sol!

items.name: Ceremonial Thorax of Qaldin
items.item_description: Behold! This ritual adornment celebrates the flawless power of the Djinn who first poured the Sentient Sand into a suit of magical armor. Flawless and mighty, like the Djinn itself, a thorax for only the most sacred of occasions.

items.name: Ceremonial Crawlers of Qaldin
items.item_description: All the rites of Qaldin are done as dance, with each step prescribed and enacted in precise detail. A misstep can mean an age of misfortune. But Sand King has never put one crawler wrong.

items.name: Staff of the Crystalline Queen
items.item_description: Locked frozen in a glacier for a thousand years, this great staff was carved long ago in honor of the twin northern stars.

items.name: Mask of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: The contract for the head of the Crimson Cut-throat was one of the most difficult that Gondar had ever accepted.  It was only natural that he'd keep a few souvenirs.

items.name: Guard of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: The guard is built from the shield and straps taken from the corpse of the Crimson Cut-throat.

items.name: Cape of the Crystalline Queen
items.item_description: Nights are cold in the contested lands, but for some, not cold enough.  This frost-charmed cape keeps cold what the sun would warm.

items.name: Stryff the Owlion
items.item_description: Nothing moves more quietly, nothing strikes harder, than this feathered prowler of the Nightsilver Woods!

items.name: Snowdrop Hood
items.item_description: Able to withstand the toughest onslaughts with nary a hair out of place, the Maiden of the North gives truth to the old adage that looks can kill.

items.name: Mantle of the Crystalline Queen
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Direstone Crown
items.item_description: Much like Morphling, the Direstone fell to earth. It is his pride to raise it high once again in this glorious crown.

items.name: Edge of the Slain Dragon
items.item_description: There is no edge so keen as the edge of a dragon slayer's sword.

items.name: Buttercup
items.item_description: The dead of battle can breed many an odd fungus.  That suits Buttercup just fine.

items.name: Buttercup's Barding
items.item_description: It is a strange thing that such a calm and gentle creature as Buttercup be made to seem so fierce.

items.name: Direstone Pauldrons
items.item_description: What smith dared forge these Direstone pauldrons, we may never know. But Morphling wears them with pride.

items.name: Wraps of a Thousand Faces
items.item_description: Hands are a warrior's greatest treasure. He must guard them well.

items.name: Sash of Death's Bride
items.item_description: When she departed, Death's Bride left little to her young apprentice.

items.name: Brooch of Death's Bride
items.item_description: No stories remain of the woman who taught Krobelus her skill, only heirlooms and rumor.

items.name: The Soul Reaper
items.item_description: The plagued dying threw themselves at Rotund'jere, offering their very souls for deliverance.  He was only too happy to accept.

items.name: Ghost Orb of the Planeswalker
items.item_description: The wayward spirits and wights lost between the planes soon become minerals to be mined and forged.

items.name: Heirloom of the Temple Priestess
items.item_description: A gilded keepsake from her first assassination, this heirloom once graced the flowing locks of Queens.  Now Templar Assassin wears it as reminder that no one is beyond her reach.

items.name: Hakama of a Thousand Faces
items.item_description: A traditional hakama from Isle of Masks. It was given to Yurnero by his late swordmaster, long before his exile.

items.name: Revered Bracers
items.item_description: This heirloom is old and cracked, yet for Azwraith it smells of home.

items.name: Crests of Polymorphia
items.item_description: The power of Polymorphia is but barely contained between these splendid crests, and takes its most awe-inspiring form in the shape of their devoted wearer, Morphling.

items.name: Crown of Polymorphia
items.item_description: Morphling emulates the eternal patterns of Polymorphia in all he does. And by this crown, he marks himself a master of the art.

items.name: Saberhorn's Pauldron
items.item_description: The sigil of Saberhorn's army is carved into the shoulder.

items.name: Saberhorn's Belt
items.item_description: This belt once belonged to Saberhorn, a legendary general from a bygone era.

items.name: Saberhorn's Heavy Chopper
items.item_description: The legendary general Saberhorn was said to have been able to end any duel with a single swing.

items.name: Barrel Quiver
items.item_description: Recycled from scraps of old wine casks, this quiver is the ultimate in green construction.

items.name: Revered Wrap
items.item_description: A belt handed down through generations; the meaning of the sigil at its center has been lost to time.

items.name: Pauldrons of Polymorphia
items.item_description: Water, they say, has a memory--but Morphling's dissolves with every form he takes. These pauldrons serve as a reminder of his original being, rooted in Polymorphia.

items.name: Kataginu of a Thousand Faces
items.item_description: A traditional sleeveless jacket worn by the great warriors of Isle of Masks. It carries the banner of Yurnero.

items.name: Mysterious Vagabond's Pack
items.item_description: His old master said, "Be clear what you are about, for these simple village folk read menace and evil intent into poor communication." Therefore Rhasta created a simple visual menu of the services he offers, and wears it in plain sight.

items.name: Feudal Mace of Chivalry
items.item_description: Prove your chivalry by smashing enemies in the face with this powerful weapon.

items.name: Hammer of Enlightenment
items.item_description: It may not save their souls, but this hammer will surely send your enemies to their just reward.

items.name: Runed Helm of Valor
items.item_description: A helm of great beauty and strength, the Runed Helm of Valor is armor worthy of the Omniknight.

items.name: Mysterious Vagabond's Wand
items.item_description: A final twist of the serpent completes Rhasta's disguise, in case he is travelling incognito. It must be admitted that sometimes he wields it just because he likes the companionship.

items.name: Mysterious Vagabond's Hat
items.item_description: "A shaman must take good care of his skin!" Rhasta's master instructed. "Therefore, always wear a hat to keep off the sun, and no less the evil influence of the moon." And then the old man always broke into laughter. "And if you believe that, I have a bag of herbs here that will confer infinite wealth and immortality."

items.name: Bow of the Crystal Caves
items.item_description: Beneath her secret glades, Drow found a passage lit by crystal shards. Following the glittering light to the farthest cavern, she discovered this bow, embedded in the rock as if it had formed there.

items.name: Mysterious Vagabond's Concoction
items.item_description: Although some travelling shaman have been rightly accused of selling colored water as if it were a certain cure for all ills, Rhasta makes no such claims and has never charged so much as a pence for a swig from this bottle. In fact, no one but Rhasta may drink from it. The Shadow Shaman's brew is certain death to anyone but its maker.

items.name: Bracers of the Crystalline Queen
items.item_description: Hard as ice, but strong as steel, these bracers bring a chill to the heart of those who would oppose the maiden of the north.

items.name: Riftshadow Roamer's Wearin' Vest
items.item_description: An extra layer or two ought to be able turn back some teeth.

items.name: Bracers of Polymorphia
items.item_description: In battle, these bracers, ever before Morphling's gaze, remind him of the power of Polymorphia.

items.name: Riftshadow Roamer's Fryin' Pan
items.item_description: Keeping a pan handy will let you make noise and scare off the wildlife, or cook them if you're lucky.

items.name: The Elder Shield
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Mask of a Thousand Faces
items.item_description: A ceremonial mask worn on special occasions. This must be a special occasion.

items.name: Bow of the Sun Vine
items.item_description: This beautiful bow, modeled after the delicate and poisonous sun vine, is even more deadly than its namesake.

items.name: Riftshadow Roamer's Fine n' Fancy
items.item_description: It can get rainy up in Riftshadow. Best bring along a hat if you want to keep your head dry.

items.name: Frost Shard Crown
items.item_description: Morphling spent eternities travelling space in the form of ice. Morphling knows ice. You know that if Morphling wears a crown of ice, it is a serious crown.

items.name: Frost Shard Pauldrons
items.item_description: The glitter of the interstellar ice that once bedizened Morphling, decks his shoulders now as he surges to and fro across the field of battle.

items.name: Furyblade
items.item_description: A thousand lives it claimed before it shattered, and a thousand more it shall claim after!

items.name: Furyblade - Off-Hand
items.item_description: A thousand lives it claimed before it shattered, and a thousand more it shall claim after!

items.name: Heavy Steel Axe
items.item_description: Forged for a brutal warlord who sought to challenge Axe in single combat.

items.name: Frost Shard Armlets
items.item_description: Coming through! Even Juggernaut will leap to avoid the icy edges of these lethal armlets.

items.name: Riftshadow Roamer's Grabbin' Wraps
items.item_description: They're not fancy, but they keep the hands warm.

items.name: Omniscient's Maul
items.item_description: For those who doubt the Omniscient One's peaceful nature, one look at this weapon proves that doubt well deserved.

items.name: Lantern of Death's Last Light
items.item_description: With this lantern Warlock peers into the shadows of death itself.  Death shrinks from the light.

items.name: Infectious Amalgamate
items.item_description: Beyond time lie stones and crystals forever able to bestow incredible power.  As these crystals leave their stasis, a growth that has never before known the temporal flow begins to take hold.

items.name: Snowdrop Mantle
items.item_description: For those times when giving someone the cold shoulder is only the beginning.

items.name: Revered Spear
items.item_description: This stone spear seems old and chipped, yet this heirloom is still very sturdy.

items.name: Snowdrop Mittens
items.item_description: Crystal Maiden hardly needs to keep her hands warm in freezing weather. We suspect these are strictly a fashion statement.

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Tusks
items.item_description: As his pick found its purchase the ice began to crack and shatter, and Tusk was sent back to the icy tundra below.

items.name: Snowdrop Tassels
items.item_description: No Wolf of Icewrack tail was harmed in the making of these tassels. They are formed entirely of soft, fluffy ice.

items.name: Dragonblood Ravager
items.item_description: Constructed from the scales and teeth of grand dragon Vyxia, her fiery blood still stains and heats the edge.

items.name: Snowdrop Staff
items.item_description: Not one for outward displays of force, Crystal Maiden understands the necessity of putting on a show. This brilliant staff is but a symbol of her inner power, and for all its luster, barely hints at the depths of her mastery.

items.name: The Blood Shard
items.item_description: On rare occasions, Skeleton King finds himself able to appreciate items that are not made of bone.

items.name: Pyre
items.item_description: Give up hope and cast yourself upon the blazing Pyre!

items.name: Falcon's Rise
items.item_description: The Skywrath revere all avian species, and hold the falcon in particularly high esteem.

items.name: The Azure Shroud
items.item_description: Skywrath Mage cowls himself in the blue of the sky above the Ghastly Eyrie

items.name: The Storm Rider's Sight
items.item_description: An eye for an eye, and a storm for his enemies; no foe can escape the piercing glare of the storm rider.

items.name: The Storm Rider's Bracer
items.item_description: This armor comes from an age long forgotten, and it crackles with the ancient power of the stormrider.

items.name: Revered Shoulder
items.item_description: Built from old leather and stone, this garment is a reminder of a simpler time.

items.name: Mancatcher of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: The Crimson Cut-throat kept a wide assortment of ornate blades to do his work.  Once the contract was complete, Gondar helped himself.

items.name: Crystalline Sickles
items.item_description: A rack of sickle curved horns for Leshrac.

items.name: Lyralei's Breeze
items.item_description: The only warning your enemies will receive will be the slight breeze that puffs their cheek as the arrow that kills them finds its mark.

items.name: Stormthrasher
items.item_description: The power of the summer squalls lays a thrashing on the enemies of Disruptor.

items.name: The Storm Rider's Deflector
items.item_description: Found in an ancient temple in Druud, this armor turns away blades and spells.  Storms are not so easily deflected.

items.name: Makeshift Hornwood Bow
items.item_description: A marvel of inventiveness, this makeshift bow proves that Windrunner can kill you without fancy weapons.  In fact, all she needs is a few sticks bound together in the shape of a bow.

items.name: Bracers of the Drake
items.item_description: Made from the scales of a drake's underbelly, this light and colorful armor is an honor to wear into battle.

items.name: Merciless Spear
items.item_description: Built to strike into the core of an adversary, and tear it apart when withdrawn.

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Hood
items.item_description: In the darkest nights of icy winter, the wolves of Icewrack howl their dirge.

items.name: Cape of the Drake
items.item_description: A long cape designed in honor of all drakes who have died in battle.

items.name: Armor of the Drake
items.item_description: Armor made from the likeness of a fallen drake.

items.name: Traveler's Jug
items.item_description: Made from the finest crushed and reconstituted dragon-hardened shell, the Traveler's Jug has for generations been thought unbreakable.  Now Brewmaster puts it to the test.

items.name: Aegis of the Storm
items.item_description: As storms are born and die upon the plains of Druud, only to be born again next season, so too is the Order of the Stormrider eternal.

items.name: Pads of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: By the time Gondar was finished, little else remained of the Crimson Cut-throat's armor.

items.name: Rampant the Scaled Hunter
items.item_description: Astride the last of the legendary archtyrex, a skilled stormcrafter channels the fury of the storm itself.

items.name: Peregrine Lance
items.item_description: As the peregrine flies, so too shall this blade.

items.name: Staff of the Archivist
items.item_description: The measured thud of this staff may be heard in the labyrinthine corridors of the Ultimyr Archives as often as these ominous words: "Now where did I put that book?"

items.name: Blade of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: The Crimson Cut-throat made no demands, and had no agenda.  The cost for his contract was paid for by the families of his victims.

items.name: Shroud of the Archivist
items.item_description: Prevents cranial intrusions by a particularly pernicious form of bookwyrm that skulks in the Ultimyr Archives.

items.name: Helmet of the Drake
items.item_description: Said to be forged from the iron that once chained the last of the great Drakinds, this helm is most coveted among dragon slayers.

items.name: Demonbag of the Archivist
items.item_description: "All Who Borrow Must Return" is the Archivist's slogan. Those who do not return what they borrow are soon visited by that which resides in this bag.

items.name: Markswoman's Cap
items.item_description: Having a bad hair day?  No problem.  This snappy little markswoman's cap is stylish for all occasions.

items.name: Robe of the Archivist
items.item_description: Resistant to mold, mildew, cobwebs, curses and other things which make perusing the Ultimyr Archives dangerous to even experienced browsers.

items.name: Lantern of the Archivist
items.item_description: Certain tomes in the Ultimyr Archives have never seen the light of day, and never will. But their pages have seen this light many times.

items.name: Armor of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: A vest made heavy and durable by materials said to repel the sorceric arts.

items.name: Bracers of the Archivist
items.item_description: For turning pages that wish not to be turned, the Archivist's bracers have been imbued with persuasive powers.

items.name: Grand Mantle of the Archivist
items.item_description: Caring for a repository of singular, priceless, unreproducible volumes of wisdom and madness is a burden that, like this mantle, may be shouldered by only an Archivist of similarly singular power.

items.name: Ring of the Storm
items.item_description: A faded alloy ring attracts static electricity.

items.name: Wings of the Ruby Web
items.item_description: Wings woven with the silk of the Deep Ruby Spider. Adorned at the tips with the gems hewn from the spider's body.

items.name: Birot's Bracers of Dignity
items.item_description: A carapaced lord of the deepest flooded oceans of the world, Birot pays tribute to water's finest representative on land.

items.name: Royal Halberd
items.item_description: Nine lances were left on the field for the nine royal guardsmen slain in the final battle against the Dread Magus.

items.name: The Stinger
