items.item_description: This one is gonna sting a little.  Oh, yes.

items.name: Shield of the Drake
items.item_description: Although forged from silver and jeweled with crimsonstone, this enchanted Shield of the Drake is no ornamental bauble to hefted at tourneys.  It is the deepest kind of magic, and its bearer could find no better protection.

items.name: Ornate Mantle of Renewed Faith
items.item_description: The massive shoulders of Omniknight bear this armor well.

items.name: Shuriken of the Crimson Cut-throat
items.item_description: Among the many weapons in the Crimson Cut-throat's home were a trio of small, curved knives which Gondar repurposed into a new shuriken.

items.name: Headdress of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_description: It has been long since this apparel has been seen in the great halls of the Slithereen, but few have forgotten it.

items.name: Heavy Steel Shoulder
items.item_description: The warlord thought his forged armor would win the day.  Axe showed him otherwise.

items.name: Spade of the Gluttonous
items.item_description: Though crafted in symbolic likeness to the great wheel books of the ruined city, the Spade of the Gluttonous whistles no song but the song of death.

items.name: Spetum of the Disciplined
items.item_description: While a sharp point may make a weapon dangerous, it takes a disciplined arm to make it deadly.

items.name: Spinal Slicer - Off-Hand
items.item_description: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.

items.name: Spinal Slicer
items.item_description: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.

items.name: Tail Fins of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_name: Tail Fins of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_description: Naga dons these noble fins, and recalls the glory days in which they slithered up the grand stairs of the sunken palace.

items.name: Heavy Steel Belt
items.item_description: A deep scratch shows at its center, a remnant of the only attack the original owner was able to deflect.

items.name: Shoulderpads of the Falcon
items.item_description: Only a diving falcon can hope to avoid Windrunner's arrows.  But this one didn't.

items.name: Warhammer of Renewed Faith
items.item_description: If ever you doubt in the power of the Omniscient, this warhammer will renew your faith.

items.name: Armlet of Renewed Faith
items.item_description: An armlet worthy of of a knight of the Omniscient.

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Snack
items.item_description: Never brave the white without a snack!

items.name: Arctic Hunter's Glove
items.item_description: What it lacks in heft it more than makes up for in tactile precision.

items.name: Hood of Defiance
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Cercus of Whirling Death
items.item_description: Sandking uses these pincers as another set of hands, grappling onto prey as they scuttle above his sandy hideaway.

items.name: Feathered Naginata
items.item_description: A light spear, balanced for quick slashes.

items.name: Sword of the Drake
items.item_description: One of only a dozen swords in existence known to have slain more than one dragon.

items.name: Verdant Coif
items.item_description: A beautiful hood in the style of the falconers of old.

items.name: Dress of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_description: Garb designed for courtly wear, Naga shows her fearless ferocity by wearing it to war.

items.name: Maiden of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_description: "Will you die to the Maiden, or to the Mistress?" Pity whoever hears this final lyric.

items.name: Cape of Thunderwrath's Calling
items.item_description: Only those who are called in service to the Omniscient can wear a cape such as this.

items.name: Helm of Thunderwrath's Calling
items.item_description: A stylish and dramatic helm truly fitting a knight of the Omniscient.

items.name: Mistress of the Slithereen Nobility
items.item_description: "My Mistress, your Master," sings Naga as her enemies bow, never to rise.

items.name: Twisted Lightbringer
items.item_description: Warlock brings light into the world with this twisted confluence of iron and magic.

items.name: Assistant's Respirator
items.item_description: This mask is not meant to keep toxic gasses out, it's meant to keep them in!

items.name: Cape of the Wind Leaf
items.item_description: A cape for all weather, this is a garment that any falconer would be proud to wear.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Shield
items.item_description: Is that the eyes of the Crimson Wyvern that peer out from this ancient shield?  I think it is.

items.name: Hammer of Thunderwrath's Calling
items.item_description: A weapon capable of hammering the most unmalleable of unbelievers into shape.

items.name: Armor of Thunderwrath's Calling
items.item_description: Armored only with your faith in the Omnicient...is not the way to go.  Also, use real armor.  Like this.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Helm
items.item_description: A helm forged in the likeness of the ancient Crimson Wyvern.

items.name: Horns of the Wicked Succubus
items.item_description: From deepest twilight come temptations dark and terrifying.

items.name: Hellish Gemstaff
items.item_description: Each facet of the gem reflects the captured soul of a bound demon.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Skirt
items.item_description: Protect your legs with the skirt of the Crimson Wyvern.  You are manly enough to pull it off; you're a knight after all.

items.name: Zaru'Kina Protector's Cape
items.item_description: Named after her village that was destroyed in a storm long ago, this cape is a reminder that wind can protect as well as destroy.

items.name: Zaru'Kina Protector's Bow
items.item_description: Named in honor of her lost village, this bow is a reminder of the destructive power of the wind.

items.name: Zaru'Kina Protector's Pads
items.item_description: Traditional protective shoulder armor commonly worn by the Zaru'Kina people.

items.name: Molten Fracture
items.item_description: Doom's power has shattered this blade.

items.name: Smashing Brawler's Shirt
items.item_description: Oy, better wear this shirt before it's full of holes!

items.name: Brawler's Hard Helm
items.item_description: He always was a hard-head. Now he's even harder.

items.name: Proof of Courage
items.item_description: In the Red Mist army, cowards were made to cut their hair in shame.  Axe has known neither fear, nor shame.  Nor a barber.

items.name: Blade of Chaos Incarnate
items.item_description: Chaos comes to earth. Chaos rides you down.

items.name: Little Blink Dagger
items.item_description: "Don't worry, precious Axe. Blink Dagger does not come to chop."

items.name: The Peacebringer
items.item_description: He brings the peace, and then he keeps it.

items.name: The Shell Slicer
items.item_description: Even those who huddle inside their tight-shut shells cannot consider themselves safe from Slark.

items.name: Ring Spear of Soul Diffusion
items.item_description: A spear forged from magical alloys that hone the mind and diffuse the soul.

items.name: Encore
items.item_description: He only wanted to hear her song one more time. The dagger was gifted to him, and he keeps it with him to silence those who wish to silence her song.

items.name: Whirling Mind Slicer
items.item_description: Blades so sharp, they might cut the very fabric of one's mind.

items.name: Birot's Crests of Dignity
items.item_description: Birot of the Deep Waters, than whom no lord is more dignified, grants a portion of his dignity to his favored Morphling, in the form of stately crests.

items.name: The Horned Mother
items.item_description: Wielding this immense weapon, Bradwarden slashes and crushes all those in his wake.

items.name: Birot's Helm of Dignity
items.item_description: Morphling proudly sports the polished and most dignified helm of Birot, who knows nothing of the dry surface world except what Morphling tells him.

items.name: Crown of the Falling Comet
items.item_description: From darkness, the comet came carrying the wotery essence of Morphling. As it fell, a searing crown marked its encounter with the atmosphere. Morphling wears it now.

items.name: Winged Paladin's Gauntlet
items.item_description: A Gauntlet as strong as faith itself, and as protective as the loving embrace of the Omniscient.

items.name: Crests of the Falling Comet
items.item_description: As the comet fell, the power of Morphling crested. Perfect for slicing through enemies as you shoulder them aside.

items.name: Tiara of the Crystalline Queen
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Bindings of the Summoned Lord
items.item_description: Ozh acha domosh ahm'omoz!

items.name: Dirk of the Wicked Succubus
items.item_description: To poke, to prod, to bleed, to destroy.

items.name: Wings of the Wicked Succubus
items.item_description: In beauty there is pain.  In pain there is beauty.

items.name: Gazing Eye of the Demon Witch
items.item_name: Gazing Eye of the Demon Witch
items.item_description: To look past reality and view the vile powers beyond requires vision and clarity surpassing most mortal means.

items.name: Scepter of the Sable Void
items.item_description: To harness the powers of the burning nether requires a symbol feared for its malice.

items.name: Ruby Ring of Rak-noth Rak-nul
items.item_description: The ring would scorch the very soul of the wearer were it not placed on a finger already beyond hope.

items.name: Belt of the Golden Mane
items.item_description: As the face upon the belt gleams in the sun, so too do the emeralds in its eyes.  The honors of the Golden Mane are valuable beyond measure.

items.name: Zaru'Kina Protector's Hair
items.item_description: A hairstyle common to the Zaru'Kina people of Windrunner's destroyed village.

items.name: Bloodwood Arc
items.item_description: Carved from the corewood of a five-thousand-year-old-tree, this magnificent brings an ancient strength to any battle.

items.name: Wraps of the Wicked Succubus
items.item_description: One must bring the appropriate attire to a battle.  To a massacre, however...

items.name: Decorative Armor of the Bone Scryer
items.item_name: Decorative Armor of the Bone Scryer
items.item_description: Death Prophet clearly has only one thing on her mind: Death. This armor holds her like a cold, bony embrace.

items.name: Gilded Falcon Bow
items.item_description: An ancient bow of oak and iron, gilded with the golden feathers of a sacred falcon.

items.name: Gilded Falcon Quiver
items.item_description: As the diving bird of prey has talons, so the archer has arrows.  And many are the arrows that can be held in the quiver of the gilded falcon.

items.name: Gilded Falcon Cloak
items.item_description: This beautiful emrald cloak is embroidered with the ancient sidgel of the gilded falcon.

items.name: Ancient Crasher
items.item_description: These dusty old blades find use once more.

items.name: Ancient Crescent
items.item_description: These dusty old blades find use once more.

items.name: Feral the Werebat
items.item_description: Werebat? There bat!

items.name: Skullsplitter Axe
items.item_description: Axe never had the heart to wipe the original owner's blood from the edge.

items.name: Gilded Falcon Helm
items.item_description: A helm of great strength and beauty, this armor of the gilden falcon offers a special kind of security, protecting both the wearer's head and identity.

items.name: Winged Paladin's Armor
items.item_description: Winged armor worthy of a knight in the great Omniscient's army.

items.name: Bloodwood Reserve
items.item_description: A beautiful quiver of the finest polished bloodwood.

items.name: Gilded Falcon Wings
items.item_description: Like the angvols of old legends, these golden falcon wings speed Windrunner's flight into battle.

items.name: Shield of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: Whatever magic his enemies use, whatever spells his foes may cast in his direction, bounce soundlessly off this shield of silence.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Shoulders
items.item_description: Constructed from the scales of a fallen wyvern, this shoulder armor is a mark of distinction for any knight.

items.name: Bracers of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: These bracers bespeak a man who will brook no magical manipulations!

items.name: Scythe of Vyse
items.item_description: The most guarded relic of the cult of Vyse, it is a weapon coveted for its magical properties.

items.name: Helm of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: Silence is golden, as is the point on this mighty helm.

items.name: Bow of the Oyoloe
items.item_description: Once thought to be a mythical beast, Windrunner slew the elusive, green oyoloe, and made a bow from its antlers.

items.name: Robe of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: No one wears this robe with quite the grandeur and majesty of Silencer. But if they do, no one will ever hear about it.

items.name: Armored Exoskeleton Arms
items.item_description: Weaver is armed and ready.  To kill you.

items.name: Shoulders of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: When a heavy silence falls, Nortrom will need mighty shoulders such as these to bear up under its weight.

items.name: Glaive of the Hidden Talent
items.item_description: With this three-bladed glaive, Nortrom ensures a silence that will never be broken.

items.name: Blade of the Slithereen Exile
items.item_description: These blades were taken from the corpses of slain leviathans following the battle of Crey.

items.name: Armlets of the Falling Comet
items.item_description: As if knowing the destiny that awaited it, the comet that once carried Morphling from the heavens produced from its own substance a pair of armlets that would one day fit its passenger perfectly.

items.name: Spear of the Golden Mane
items.item_description: To wield such a prized spear, one must have courage and ferocity befitting the honors of the Golden Mane.

items.name: Gauntlet of the Golden Mane
items.item_description: To gain the honors of the Golden Mane, one must endure incredible sacrifice.

items.name: Shoulder of the Golden Mane
items.item_description: In each ferocious face is set determination without fear.  Such is required from those who would don the honors of the Golden Mane.

items.name: Helm of the Slithereen Exile
items.item_description: Stripped of her rank and station, the exile Slithice has been instructed to cover her headfin while among her people.

items.name: Armor of the Slithereen Exile
items.item_description: Fashioned in the forge of an undersea volcano, the obsidian plating was a given to Slithice as a gift from the grateful denizens of Crey.

items.name: Winged Paladin's Glorious Cape
items.item_description: A glorious cape sewn by a hundred monks in honor of the Omniscient.

items.name: Winged Paladin's Helm
items.item_description: A helm of purest gold and sterling silver, created in honor of the Omniscient.

items.name: Skins of the Incubus
items.item_description: Few facets of the utter foul wander the land unbidden. To claim such a skin is to declare primacy over the inferno.

items.name: Spear of the Herald
items.item_description: An ancient weapon from an unknown craftsman, it was said to have been forged for he whom destiny calls worthy. Each swing heralds another step toward a new age.

items.name: Winged Paladin's Defiance
items.item_description: Defy the Omniscient, and the price will be this blade on your neck.  It is a heavy weapon, wielded with a heavy heart.

items.name: Shroud of the Shattered Sect
items.item_description: To possess the power of a Demon Witch is to stand in defiance of powers seen and unseen.

items.name: Heart of the Inauspicious Abyss
items.item_description: Those who patrol the edge of the void must gird themselves in armor impregnable to evil's piercing rays.

items.name: Wings of the Inauspicious Abyss
items.item_description: As the threat from the outer dark mounts, the Harbinger intimidates these implacable forces with wings of strange power.

items.name: Shredder of the Vandal
items.item_description: If you run out of arrows, you can always stab your enemies with this.  It has more points than Leshrac has horns.

items.name: Wraps of the Seasoned Veteran
items.item_description: Spending time on the trail is bound to take its toll sooner or later.

items.name: Torn Guard of the Vandal
items.item_description: Tired of your clavicle being exposed to the world?  Here is an enchanted armor designed to shield old bones from plight of combat.

items.name: Dark Quiver of the Vandal
items.item_description: Endless arrows shall be pulled from the pouch over your shoulder.  Enemies will quiver at the sight.

items.name: Ambinderath's Jaw
items.item_description: The severed jaw of the undead dragon Ambinderath. The dragon once opposed the Skeleton King's eastern expansion.

items.name: Bessy the Batmeleon
items.item_description: The Rider found this exotic creature trying to blend in with a colony of morde-bats before he tamed it for his own.

items.name: The Instagib OSP
items.item_description: The Instagib 'Optimal Shooting Platform' is a highly tuned, perfectly balanced brain liquification device.

items.name: Great Grey Owl Bow
items.item_description: She dreamed in the night that the divine owl spirit called her name. When she woke, this bow lay beside her in a bed of leaves...grey feathers still drifting from the branch above.

items.name: Belt of Claszureme
items.item_description: Upon the dial at its center lie markings which map the way to the realms beyond time.

items.name: Bracers of Claszureme
items.item_description: The spikes on the wrist are said to sample the flow of time, while the runes report the findings to the wearer.

items.name: Sparrowhawk Bow
items.item_description: Strong, but light as a feather, this bow of the sparrowhawk will fly your arrows true to their targets.

items.name: Shoulders of Claszureme
items.item_description: For a traveler from Claszureme, one's place in the flow of time is uncertain.  These runes help ground the wearer within time's march.

items.name: Demon Spine Recurve Bow
items.item_description: Made from the vertebrae of the fallen damned, this bow is crooked as the spine of any demon.

items.name: Sparrowhawk Cape
items.item_description: In addition to being stylish, this cape of the sparrowhawk manages the trick of also being camouflaging, provided that you're standing next to a flock of sparrowhawks.

items.name: Maw of the Devourer
items.item_description: From the World at the Rim, this staff is a weighty reminder of the howling void that waits for us all.

items.name: Sparrowhawk Hood
items.item_description: It takes a spectacular hood to tame your fiery red hair.

items.name: Jeweled Longbow
items.item_description: Simple and elegant, set off perfectly by gems of uncommon brilliance. On examination, the workmanship is that of a race long thought extinct. How then is this bow brand new?

items.name: Demon Guise of the Vandal
items.item_description: For a hundred years, a blind smeevil hammered and honed his masterpiece, until the great work was done.  None shall see your face behind the iron mask of the Demon Guise.

items.name: Ancient Slithereen Basher
items.item_description: Few are the weapons that have outlasted the wars beneath the waves.

items.name: Sparrowhawk Wings
items.item_description: Tired of your shoulders being devoid of sparrowhawk feathers?  Then this item is for you.

items.name: Chained Snatcher
items.item_description: Never give a meal the chance to be late for dinner.

items.name: Chained Chopper
items.item_description: Tangled in the links of Pudge's chains, a reminder of the shackles that bind us to life--and how easily Pudge may break them.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Bracers
items.item_description: Made from the interlocking scales that sit above the wyvern's spine, this crimson bracer is a perfect fit for knight's forearm.

items.name: Crimson Riptide
items.item_description: Let this blade drink deep of your foe.

items.name: Crimson Wyvern Sword
items.item_description: A sword made from the talons of a fallen wyvern.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Boots
items.item_description: The guardians of the forest paths walk in perfect silence, betrayed not by their cunning footwear.

items.name: Mallet of Magnificence
items.item_description: The go-to mallet for when your enemies absolutely, positively must be smited.

items.name: Golden Riptide
items.item_description: Let this blade guard you from harm.

items.name: Fishing Halberd
items.item_description: Off the coast near the village of Pole are fish large enough to eat a man in a single bite.  Against such a beast, a spear simply will not do.

items.name: Finblade
items.item_description: Kunkka's ship cleaves the waves as easily as Finblade cleaves his enemies. Kunkka revels in the iridiscent play of light given off by dashing spray and liberated souls alike.

items.name: Bow of the Searing Soul
items.item_description: A bow brought back from hell itself.   With this weapon, enemies will feel the searing burn of your anger.

items.name: Sparrowhawk Quiver
items.item_description: Proving that every part of the sparrowhawk can be turned into a stylish item for Windrunner to wear, this quiver speaks to the utility of sparrowhawks as a species.

items.name: Tail of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The third curse, curse of the prehensile, lain upon his tail.

items.name: Scythe of Pestilence
items.item_description: Plague and pestilence are the Reaper's trusty tools for harvesting souls.

items.name: Hammer of Light Inexorable
items.item_description: This strange, rune-scrawled hammer will ensure that all your enemies see the light.

items.name: Sword of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The first curse, the curse of flame, lain upon his sword.

items.name: Horns of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The eleventh and final curse, the curse of wisdom, lain upon his horns.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Bow
items.item_description: Drow has nothing to learn from the Sylvan Guard, but from time to time she relieves one of them of their bow, that she might test its quality. Even by her standards, this one is adjudged very fine.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Cape
items.item_description: Stealth is of utmost importance to those who number themselves among the Sylvan Guard. Even Drow finds this an acceptable cape for moving unseen through the wooded ways.

items.name: Bracer of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The sixth curse, the curse of fortitude, lain upon his wrists.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Hair
items.item_description: While not a member of the Sylvan Guard, Drow spies upon them in their marches, and occasionally admires their passing fashions.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Quiver
items.item_description: The archers of the Sylvan Guard shoot only arrows crafted specifically for their use. When Drow uses their gear, such arrows are de rigeur.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Cuffs
items.item_description: In her youth, Drow was tempted once or twice to throw over her lonely ways and join the Sylvan Guard. These cuffs were a large part of the attraction.

items.name: Wings of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The second curse, the curse of the fallen, is lain upon his wings.

items.name: Sylvan Guard's Dress Armor
items.item_description: It must be admitted: Drow admires the Sylvan Guard. When from time to time she puts on their gear, and pretends to adopt their ways, she can hardly suppress her joy in having an excuse to don this stylish armor.

items.name: The Half Measure
items.item_description: The other blade was just for show.

items.name: Belt of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: A belt of cursed power.  Would that the navel of the world were so protected.

items.name: Armored Exoskeleton Back
items.item_description: Thick plates of armored chitin protect you from the attack of your enemies.

items.name: Armored Exoskeleton Wings
items.item_description: With these wings, your final transformation is complete.

items.name: Armored Exoskeleton Legs
items.item_description: Even your legs are armed.

items.name: Holy Spear of Images
items.item_description: In each blade is reflected an army.  In each strike is reflected an ideal.

items.name: Shoulder of the Eleven Curses
items.item_description: The tenth curse, the curse of strength, is lain upon his shoulders, like all the weight of the world.

items.name: Ishul-Shog the Watcher
items.item_description: Demnok studied for years to construct the true name of the Watcher, hoping to bind a creature powerful enough to know and reveal the Ozkavosh tongue.  Unfortunately, the Watcher lacks a tongue.

items.name: Auspex of the Inauspicious Abyss
items.item_description: A helm whose very symmetry foreshadows the dark power that Harbinger may summon to protect the inmost shells of creation from cold destructive forces beyond knowing.

items.name: Thyrsus of the Inauspicious Abyss
items.item_description: On the world at the rim grow a species of crystalline tree in whose branches visions of the future are tangled. From such a tree, Outworld Devourer fashioned this staff.

items.name: Loner's Vanity
items.item_description: "And why shouldn't I?" Drow has been heard to say, to absolutely no one.

items.name: Hair of the Dark Magic
items.item_description: Style and sorcery are said to go hand in hand.

items.name: Nightsilver Bracers
items.item_description: The moon's lustre fills these bracers, and fills Mirana with midnight power.

items.name: Radiant Crystal Haul
items.item_description: Gotta dig deep if you want to find the best!

items.name: Cape of the Dark Magic
items.item_description: To the Invoker, those without the gifts of magic are insects to be ignored or destroyed.  For at time, his ferocity was such that the magical arts were treated with superstition and fear by all.

items.name: Red Talon Hood
items.item_description: Red of hood and red of claw, this headpiece shields the Beastmaster from the elements.

items.name: Bracers of the Dark Magic
items.item_description: Those who practiced the magical arts are often feared for their power.

items.name: Shoulders of the Dark Magic
items.item_description: In an age when fear surrounded sorcery, tales told of an oppressive wizard capable of limitless destruction.

items.name: Collar of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: Those whom the Anti-Mage hunts may be as skilled with a sword as they are with a spell, and so this collar was crafted to turn their blades aside.

items.name: Bracer of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: These bracers are made to defend against both swords and sorcery.

items.name: Skirt of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: Time and practice would persuade the Anti-Mage against such a heavy garment, yet its use in combat has not diminished.

items.name: Glaive of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: Brutality defined many of the early weapons used by the Anti-Mage.

items.name: Mask of the Mage Slayer
items.item_description: The elements used in this mask's construction are able to deflect most spells, just as its shape may divert a blade.

items.name: Red Talon Guard
items.item_description: Heavy is the burden shouldered by the Beastmaster, and strong is the mantle that supports him.

items.name: Red Talon Axes
items.item_description: The last person to call these weapons primitive ended up wearing one in his skull.

items.name: Red Talon Bracers
items.item_description: A powerful bracer of leather, bone and fur.

items.name: Red Talon Belt
items.item_description: A belt of leather and feather, bound in bone.

items.name: Claw of the Haruspex
items.item_description: Serpent Clan long held to the traditions of the haruspex, and so foresaw the ruin and war that would visit the ancient clans.

items.name: Cloak of the Haruspex
items.item_description: As Serpent Clan spread word of their coming doom, they granted their honored vestments to Sylla that he may remember their words.

items.name: Gilded Mark of the Haruspex
items.item_description: Upon the shoulder sits a coiled snake, wrought in gold. The seers of Serpent Clan often read the future in the entrails of their lowly kin.

items.name: Sacrificial Blade of the Haruspex
items.item_description: The blade has seen the belly of many a beast so that knowledge may pour forth and forewarn those in need.

items.name: Torment Unbound
items.item_description: Her hair down, your queen is relaxed in her work.

items.name: Chain of Enduring Torment
items.item_description: She may be chained, but she is still in control.

items.name: Tiara of Enduring Torment
items.item_description: To give riches is torture.  To take riches is bliss.

items.name: Dagger of Enduring Torment
items.item_description: Twist once and the blood starts to spill.  Twist again and see the pleasure flow.

items.name: Scarf of the Deadly Nightshade
items.item_description: Whosoever wears this mantle, the spirit Tyrian ensures they shall shrug off any burden, while their identity and their purpose remain concealed.

items.name: Garb of the Deadly Nightshade
items.item_description: The spirit of Atropos inflicts dread and delirium on any who spy the wearer of this garb. Best not to see Lanaya at all, or even wonder at her whereabouts.

items.name: Headpiece of the Deadly Nightshade
items.item_description: Although barely visible beneath the rim of this headpiece, Belladonna grants the wearer the enormous dilated eyes that so befit a seeker of mysterious truths.

items.name: Scythe of Sacrifice
items.item_description: It is an honor to be sacrificed on Phantom Assassin's scythe.

items.name: Blade of the Black Rider
items.item_description: With blade aloft, Chaos Knight falls upon his foe like a sky of endless gloom.

items.name: Eye of the Eyrie
items.item_description: A wizardly staff bearing the Skywrath symbol of clairvoyance.

items.name: Graveheart Staff
items.item_description: At the edge of death, a spark of life remains to restart a faltering heart.

items.name: Ainidul the Eternal
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Bangles of the Wildwing's Blessing
items.item_description: The Wildwings treasure their lost feathers, saving them to line the nests where they raise their young. It speaks of their deep respect for Enchantress that they gifted her these feathers for her bangles.

items.name: Councilor's Staff
items.item_description: Any suitably imbued staff will serve for most sorcerers.  However, being an aspiring councilor requires that certain concessions be made to form.

items.name: Necklace of the Wildwing's Blessing
items.item_description: The Wildwing are fierce and territorial, but they more than tolerate Enchantress in their realms: They welcome her.

items.name: Councilor's Shawl
items.item_description: Few sorcerers can claim to own a shawl that appears as prestigious as it is fire resistant.

items.name: Councilor's Robe
items.item_description: To be at once a Magus, a duelist, and an aspiring politician requires a robe that is both stately and blast proof.

items.name: Ancestral Headdress
items.item_description: Worn by an elder shadow priest during the very founding of the Dezun Order, this skull headdress has been handed down for generations.

items.name: Ancestral Cloak
items.item_description: The elders grant this cloak only to the most skilled of the Dezun Order.

items.name: Ancestral Arm Wrap
items.item_description: To raise an arm wrapped in such a holy garment is to channel the most ancient knowledge of the Nothl Realm.

items.name: Ancestral Dress
items.item_description: Bound with rope and made of simple fabrics, this dress burns with Nothl strength.

items.name: Ancestral Medicine Stick
items.item_description: The pattern at its center is said to focus and channel the Nothl's power.

items.name: Scythe of Twin Deaths
items.item_description: Heavy with the gifts granted by the plagued nobility, Rotund'jere had this frightening tool fashioned to remind those in his care of the ever-present likelihood of their demise.

items.name: Reliquary of Rotting Doom
items.item_description: Behind the sacred vestments of this dark cardinal lies little else but rot and ruin.

items.name: Pretiosa of Putrescense
items.item_description: At the height of his corrupted influence, Rotund'jere had quite an assortment of fashionable hats.

items.name: Beard of Weeping Scorn
items.item_description: Bands made from woven silk and gold tie this tainted hair together.

items.name: Nightsilver Quiver
items.item_description: Even in the dark of a moonless night, Mirana shall not fumble for an arrow when she carries the Nightsilver Quiver.

items.name: Nightsilver Raiments
items.item_description: Draped in the dark magic of a fabric as sheer as the new moon's faintest rays, Mirana glides silently through the dark.

items.name: Nightsilver Regalia
items.item_description: Bearing a gem that reflects the brightness of the Demon Star between the moon's horns, Mirana knows no fear.

items.name: Nightsilver Locks
items.item_description: Just as the moon appears to greatest advantage in the darkest skies, Mirana's tresses shine most softly in the Nightsilver Woods.

items.name: Nightsilver Bow
items.item_description: The defense of the Nightsilver Woods relies not only on the most skilled archer, but on the blessed bow she carries.

items.name: Sash of the Third Insight
items.item_description: In the eyes beyond, all that is found must then be appraised.

items.name: Brooch of the Third Insight
items.item_description: There is little a mind cannot assess provided it is properly equipped.

items.name: Mask of the Third Insight
items.item_description: Just as what is known must be learned, what is spoken must be thought.

items.name: The Sharpshooter's Stache
items.item_description: The Keen Folk are, for the most part, a finely mustachioed people, and Sniper is no exception.  It took him nearly three days to grow out this stache.

items.name: The Killstealer
items.item_description: Among the Keen Folk, weapons are passed down from father to son, and the Killstealer was originally cast in Sniper's grandfather's day.  They just don't make 'em like they used to.

items.name: The Sharpshooter's Pauldrons
items.item_description: These shoulder pads provide protection against both the enemy, and the occasional bruised shoulder of the long-distance shootist.

items.name: The Sharpshooter's Cloak
items.item_description: A cloak is every traveler's friend.  A warm covering for the cold, and it confuses the silhouette, making the wearer a more difficult target at long range.

items.name: Slim Blade of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_name: Slim Blade of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_description: When death is the price, one can never swing too many blades.

items.name: Mask of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_description: The crest of the Tahlin Watch sits upon the brow.

items.name: Tribal Stone Edge
items.item_description: The weight of stone drives every swing.

items.name: Tribal Stone Pauldron
items.item_description: Those of the stone hills view the gift of flight as a gift from the heavens, and so arms are made to honor those that soar above.

items.name: Tribal Stone Horns
items.item_description: To the elder tribes of the stone hills, all is of hewn rock and carved edge.

items.name: Egg of the Stormcrow
items.item_description: The sacred egg of the stormcrow.  A powerful source of magic, once certain rituals have been performed.

items.name: Beak of the Stormcrow
items.item_description: A mask crafted from the beak of the stormcrow.

items.name: Cloak of the Stormcrow
items.item_description: A cloak crafted from the feathers and talons of the stormcrow.

items.name: Tail of the Stormcrow
items.item_description: A belt crafted from the tail feathers of the stormcrow.

items.name: Sigil of the Stormcrow
items.item_description: A staff bearing the sigil of the stormcrow, crafted from its sacred bones.

items.name: Ceremonial Claws of Qaldin
items.item_description: Incised with the luminous runes of Qezh, the upraised claws of the Scintillant Supplicant summon the full attention of the Djinn of Qaldin.

items.name: Ceremonial Stinger of Qaldin
items.item_description: At the height of the ceremony of Qaz'hallaq, seven virtuous acolytes are stung to death with one swipe of this malevolent armored appendage.

items.name: Sigil of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_description: Very few display the talent necessary to join the Tahlin Watch.

items.name: Bracer of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_description: As he fled his family's slaughter, Riki disguised himself with the armor of his royal watch in order to escape undetected.

items.name: Tribal Stone Vambrace
items.item_description: In the stone hills, the elder tribes endure unknown to the rest of the world.

items.name: Belt of the Bramble Lord
items.item_description: None now remember the reign of the Bramble Lord, and fewer still are the relics of that dark era.

items.name: Buckler of the Bramble Lord
items.item_description: The grim visage of the Bramble Lord adorns the deflector.

items.name: Lance of the Bramble Lord
items.item_description: The Bramble Lord insisted that all arms made in his honor be just as adept at piercing as they were at tearing.

items.name: Spaulder of the Bramble Lord
items.item_description: All who dared stand against the Bramble Lord well knew how easily his powers could catch and pierce their lives.

items.name: Blade of the Slithereen Exile - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Blade of the Slithereen Exile - Off-Hand
items.item_description: These blades were taken from the corpses of slain leviathans following the battle of Crey.

items.name: Steel Wings of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: Six and sixty times his wings were branded, but now they are seated within a chrysalis of finest armor.

items.name: Runed Bracers of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: He that burns now wears bracers is forged in the cauldron of deepest hell.

items.name: Assistant's Cutter
items.item_description: Most observers of Alchemy fail to realize the importance of personal defense against most observers of Alchemy.

items.name: The Hunter's Helm
items.item_description: A helm plucked from the battlefield, after a glorious victory over Cosang riders in the Desert of Misrule.

items.name: Cape of the Great Safari
items.item_description: Simple, elegant, ripped from a corpse.  The scap of banner taken from a Vigil Knight now makes a fine cape for a Keen.

items.name: Bracers of the Seasoned Hunter
items.item_description: Rule number one, always come prepared!

items.name: Sharpeye's Momentos
items.item_description: Sniper is an expert marksman.  Now he has the medals to prove it!

items.name: Rifle of the Great Safari
items.item_description: The latest tool in advanced marksmanship.  Guns don't kill people; Sniper kills people.

items.name: Direstone Liferipper
items.item_description: Direstone is said to be lightweight and easy to counterbalance, making it perfect for a reaper.

items.name: Ember Edge
items.item_description: Ever it glows with heat and power, a blade of warmth in the darkness, a beacon of strength on the field.

items.name: Boneslayer
items.item_description: When Ostarion came to conquer, this blade was presented as a gift in hope of negotiating a peaceful surrender.  It didn't work.

items.name: Bloodstained Britches
items.item_description: "You don't get this good at butchery without spending a bit of time on a farm."

items.name: Rotten Stache
items.item_description: 'Thought it was time to try me out a new look.  What you think?'

items.name: Mask of Dark Ferocity
items.item_description: In the bounty hunting business, a little intimidation can go a long way.

items.name: Ignited Scepter
items.item_description: As luck would have it, this enchanted cudgel was just lying there in an exploding volcano Aggron happened to have stumbled in to.

items.name: Demonhide Girdle of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: Doom's loins are girded in thickest demonhide and steel.

items.name: Steel Horns of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: Heavy is the head that wears the horns of the Apocalypse.

items.name: Royal Dagger of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_name: Royal Dagger of the Tahlin Watch
items.item_description: As old as the Tahlin Dynasty itself, this dagger has loosed blood in both war and peacetime.

items.name: Royal Dagger of the Tahlin Watch - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Royal Dagger of the Tahlin Watch - Off-Hand
items.item_description: As old as the Tahlin Dynasty itself, this dagger has loosed blood in both war and peacetime.

items.name: Bow of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_description: A jagged bow for a burning soul.

items.name: Pauldrons of the Crypt Guardian
items.item_description: These razor-sharp pauldrons bring new meaning to the term shoulder blade.

items.name: Dark Ruin Helm
items.item_description: In the molten furnace of the Ruined Keep, the blind forgemasters craft their wares.

items.name: Hellstrider
items.item_description: Where rides the knight, only chaos remains.

items.name: Dark Ruin Gaze
items.item_description: It is said the blind forgemasters of the Ruined Keep are haunted by visions of realms beyond mortal knowledge.

items.name: Dark Ruin Mantle
items.item_description: Upon the shoulders of darkness sit the burdens of chaos.

items.name: Dark Ruin Crusher
items.item_description: From mortal order to ruined chaos.

items.name: Obsidian Blade Spear
items.item_description: "There is no sharper edge in nature," is a good thing to say if you wish to try your blade in a fight.

items.name: Obsidian Blade Dagger
items.item_description: A shard from the fields of ebon glass that sealed the Petrified City of Saraddel.

items.name: Legs of the Brood Queen
items.item_description: Eight legs of armor, each hammered from the breastplate of a fallen knight.

items.name: Crown of the Brood Queen
items.item_description: With shaking hands, the doomed blacksmith laid a crown upon the spider's head, saying, "A crown fit for a queen."

items.name: Bladed Abdomen of the Brood Queen
items.item_name: Bladed Abdomen of the Brood Queen
items.item_description: Strong though her natural chitinous armor may be, there is something about the caress of steel against her carapice that privides a special sense of security for the Brood Queen.

items.name: Blessings of the Solar Divine
items.item_description: The acolytes of the Solar Goddess said Lina's hair was "touched by the light", and so gifted her with trinkets made to reflect the warming love of the sun.

items.name: Sleeves of the Solar Divine
items.item_description: During her training in the flame arts, Lina chose to travel east to study with the followers of the Solar Goddess.

items.name: Flares of the Solar Divine
items.item_description: The heat of the eastern wastes is said to be extraordinary.  One must dress appropriately.

items.name: Arc of the Solar Divine
items.item_description: It is said that in a moment of divine inspiration the Solar Goddess herself visited Lina to bless her with power, and grant her this gift.

items.name: Catalyst Cap
items.item_description: The perfect accoutrement for when Lina wishes to "Mix things up a bit." Which is almost always.

items.name: Molten Genesis
items.item_description: It takes a truly special bow to be wielded by fingers of flame.

items.name: Flesh Ripper
items.item_description: "Ah, flesh meat!"

items.name: Heavy Tenderizer
items.item_description: A few quick turns under Pudge's Tenderizer, and even the toughest foe goes down like butter.

items.name: Blade of Cleaving Swiftness
items.item_description: Cleave fast, die young, and leave an imperishable corpse!

items.name: Claive of Unyielding Stone
items.item_description: When Sven stands his ground, this blade stands with him.

items.name: Grull the Grim Walker
items.item_description: Disruptor had his eye on Grull from the moment he spotted the beast standing in the corner of the breeder's yard. "Who's that one then?" "Grull. None can ride her. She's too disruptive." "Perfect! I'll ride her home!"

items.name: Spirit of Calm
items.item_description: Though doom and ruin they saw, the visions of the haruspex brought to Sylla a sense of destined calm. During mediations, he found his spiritual projections altered to appear less intimidating.

items.name: The Commodore's Kraken Slayer
items.item_description: No mere clam-splitter, this.  Kunkk wields a fine blade of strongest steel, able to pierce Kraken hide.

items.name: The Commodore's Bicorne
items.item_description: Rain, nor waves, nor driving wind can chill Kunkka's head while he's wearing this noble cowl.

items.name: The Commodore's Curtains
items.item_description: Many a storm has sluiced down upon these broad shoulders, now protected from the stormy seas by this stylish all-weather gear.

items.name: The Commodore's Puffy Cuffs
items.item_description: Make no mistake, Kunkka is a salty old sailor not to be underestimated.  If he wears puffy cuffs, it's because he has something up his sleeve.

items.name: Fashion of Yoskreth
items.item_description: The fashions of Yoskreth are not common in much of the rest of the world.

items.name: Spellbreaker of Yoskreth
items.item_description: The sovereign of Yoskreth insisted that their champion be given the finest guard they could forge.

items.name: Ceremonial Pshent of Qaldin
items.item_description: The sentient sands of the Scintillant Waste don this glorious headpiece for only their most sacred rites.

items.name: Armguards of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_description: In penance for his transgressions Chen was made to don the arms of his new faith, and wander his former desert home seeking conversions.

items.name: Shoulderguards of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_description: The shoulderguards reflect the heavenly light above as a beacon of salvation visible from leagues away.

items.name: Turban of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_description: Those of the Hazhadal Barrens know the dangers of wearing improper headgear in the desert wastes.

items.name: Infernal Pauldrons of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: He that burns carries all the weight of the Apocalypse upon his mighty shoulders.

items.name: Locuthi Barding of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_name: Locuthi Barding of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_description: The barding is lighter both in weight and in coloring, both necessary elements for survival in the dry wastes.

items.name: Commanding Rod of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_name: Commanding Rod of the Penitent Nomad
items.item_description: Though it does not have the heft of the traditional rod, it lacks none of its potency.

items.name: Sash of Yoskreth
items.item_description: In his gratitude, the sovereign of Yoskreth bid that fine robes be made for the warrior who had bested Sahsk's vile enchantments.

items.name: Etched Crescent of Yoskreth - Off-Hand
items.item_description: With the defeat of Sahsk, the sovereign of Yoskreth granted the Anti-Mage tools befitting one of such power and skill.

items.name: Demon Blade of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: A cursed blade forged to slice through the membrane that separates the seven hells.

items.name: Etched Crescent of Yoskreth
items.item_description: With the defeat of Sahsk, the sovereign of Yoskreth granted the Anti-Mage tools befitting one of such power and skill.

items.name: Belt of Yoskreth
items.item_description: Fine cloth is combined with the silvered metals that make up the royal patterns of Yoskreth.

items.name: Tail Plates of Apocalyptic Fire
items.item_description: A stygian tail of finest demon armor, forged in the fifth of the seven hells.

items.name: Bracers of Yoskreth
items.item_description: As the Anti-Mage grew in power and prestige, the sovereign of Yoskreth sought his services to topple the fearsome sorcerer Sahsk.

items.name: Spear of the Wildwing's Blessing
items.item_description: It is unfortunate that a few rogue Wildkin must spoil the proud race's reputation, but when it is time to hunt those few rascals down, Enchantress bears a spear granted her by the wisest of the Wildwing race.

items.name: Headdress of the Wildwing's Blessing
items.item_description: Enchantress passes unchallenged through Wildwing territories when she wears this headdress.

items.name: Wingbelt of the Wildwing's Blessing
items.item_description: Fear not, this belt was crafted by Wildwing artisans from thousands of feathers plucked painlessly from living individuals; and not, as some have suggested, hacked from a dead Wildwing.

items.name: The Corrupted Shard
items.item_description: Only the doomed, or doom's master, can carry this single fragment of absolutely pure, unalloyed, unsullied corruption.

items.name: Empowering Elements
items.item_description: As light as a feather to the weilder.  The weight of a boulder to its target.

items.name: The Commodore's Facings
items.item_description: Woven from the finest, tight-knitted fabrics, this heavy chest-piece protects from both the elements and errant blades.

items.name: The Commodore's Gaiters
items.item_description: These hardy, salt-toughened boots provide firm footing whether striding a heaving deck, or a blood-soaked battlefield.

items.name: The Commodore's Sash
items.item_description: A Sash of rarest spider silk, the parting gift of a long ago princess from the isle of Songs.

items.name: The Sharpshooter's Bullet Bracers
items.item_description: Why carry your bullets in a bag when you can slot them into your bracers for quick reloading?

items.name: Fiery Soul of the Slayer
items.item_description: It has often been said that Lina's hair was touched by fire, though few know the truth of this claim.  In Lina's youth, as her natural talents first began to smoke and smolder it was her fiery hair that told the tale of the storm to come.  With time and training, her skill and control of the flame was enough to suppress the searing display.  Yet on occasion, when her ire grows and tempers flare, the full measure of Lina's burning spirit threatens to unleash its wrath.

items.name: Horn of the Hidden Hive
items.item_description: Each Nyx Assassin's third kill is marked with the bestowing of this great horn--a ceremonial piece that must be blooded repeatedly if it is to be retained.

items.name: Claws of the Hidden Hive
items.item_description: When the new Nyx Assassin is chosen, he is sent to the Hidden Hive for confirmation. These claws connote completion of the Assassin's first assignment.

items.name: Shell of the Hidden Hive
items.item_description: Only those who preside in the Hidden Hive and share in the schemes of the goddess Nyx know the true significance of this ceremonial armor.

items.name: Assistant's Blades of Scientific Inquiry
items.item_description: When the science of Alchemy requires hacking your way through a mob of angry villagers, accept nothing less.

items.name: Experimentalist's Laboratory Essentials
items.item_description: Just because you're in a battle is no reason not to practice proper lab safety!

items.name: Experimentalist's Goggles
items.item_description: Against the caustic chems involved in the average experiment, they do nothing.  But they're good for peace of mind.

items.name: Experimentalist's Unstable Flask
items.item_description: Carved and formed from Radiant ore.

items.name: Assistant's Muscle Pump
items.item_description: With its triple reinforced outer shell, it's technically safer inside this pipe than in most castles.

items.name: Arcane Staff of the Ancients
items.item_description: A staff forged in the heart of Light's own dream of itself, it has been entrusted to Light's Keeper as a manifestation of the ancient power.

items.name: The Silent Ripper
items.item_description: Perfect for sliding through the bars of a cell, for a silent shiv in the dark. Just don't ask where he hides it.

items.name: The Shattered Blade of Levinthal
items.item_description: The Duke of Levinthal, Elector of the Gleaming City, withstood Ostarion's besieging undead legions for many days before sallying forth to face the Immortal King in personal combat. This broken blade is the sole legacy of that ill-fated act of defiance.

items.name: Grampa Sharpie's Shin Shooter
items.item_description: Brag 'Whistlecheeks' Sharpeye was once the finest gun in all the Knollen, able to knock the toes off a troll at one thousand feet. He left his favorite gun to his grandson in the hopes that one day young Kardel would continue to build its legend.

items.name: Gramma Sharpie's Smokin' Rug
items.item_description: Gramma Sharpeye never touched a rifle in her life, but she rolled a fine cigar and packed a solid cartridge. Every fifth eve, after chores were done gramma would sit by the fire and puff her cigar and rock her chair and pack enough cartridges to serve the entire family's shooting. Wear her favorite smokin' rug on your back as a memento of those happy days.

items.name: Ragestone Axe
items.item_description: Veins of ragestone are well known to the keen and humans who have taken up masonry or mining. The material's strange magical influence has been known to drive men and beasts into bloody fits of madness and horrible acts of uncontrolled violence. Axe doesn't see what the problem is.

items.name: Gloried Horn of Druud
items.item_description: Encorselled by Elder Greyhoofs at the Clanfounding, a single note from this horn can call forth the great hordes of Druud to do battle at the end of all times. Bradwarden the Warrunner and vanguard of the Druud clans protects the horn and will, at the appointed hour, summon his brothers and sisters to make a final apocalyptic war.

items.name: Big Bad Bandana
items.item_description: The wind can only keep so much hair back.

items.name: Headdress of the Father Spirits
items.item_description: Fashioned from the feathers of the violet shryll, a bird that flies with its wingtips trailing through the Nothl realm, while the rest of its body sails in the light of this world.

items.name: Great Pipe of the Father Spirits
items.item_name: Great Pipe of the Father Spirits
items.item_description: There are many ways to reach the Nothl realm, several of which involve hits from the Great Pipe. Some hits are less survivable than others.

items.name: Fetish of the Father Spirits
items.item_description: When it comes to dazzling fetishes, the Father Spirit knows best.

items.name: Ritual Skirt of the Father Spirits
items.item_name: Ritual Skirt of the Father Spirits
items.item_description: What does Dazzle wear under his ritual skirt? That depends upon the ritual.

items.name: Rough Rider's Tools
items.item_description: It'll take more than a rope to tame the wilds of Yama Raskav.

items.name: Rough Rider's Slipshod Slicker
items.item_description: You'll be glad you have this when the rainy season comes around.

items.name: Rough Rider's Muggin' Mask
items.item_description: A few dips into the wilds of Yama Raskav will bring out the brigand in anyone.

items.name: Bertha the Morde-bat
items.item_description: A little sweeter to some, a little meaner to the rest, you'd best be on this beauty's good side if you aim to keep your head.

items.name: Ember Tipped Carapace
items.item_description: When the energies of creation are hot and malleable, Skitskurr's carapace responds in kind, alerting him that it is time to start weaving.

items.name: Ember Tipped Striders
items.item_description: Creep carefully along the threads of time, with these precision crafted striders.

items.name: Ember Tipped Manipulators
items.item_description: When it is time to reweave the stuff of reality, Skitskurr dons his finest manipulators.

items.name: Ember Tipped Antennae
items.item_description: Skitskurr senses are finely tuned to the slightest disruption of the fabric of creation.

items.name: Yasha the Quickblade
items.item_description: Yasha, one of two legendary moonblades, is said to take on a form that best matches its owner's chosen martial art. In the hands of Riki this weapon takes the blade of a small, well balanced dagger.

items.name: Sange the Backseeker
items.item_description: Sange, one of the two legendary moonblades, is said to be unnaturally accurate and able to change to a form that best fits the fighting style of its owner. In the hands of Riki the weapon becomes a small dagger.

items.name: Councilor's Mask
items.item_description: Rubick's foray into the often confused politics of magicians is greatly aided by this enchanted third eye. At least, that's what he claims.

items.name: Mask of Distant Sands
items.item_description: The heat of the eastern wastes is said to be extraordinary.  One must cover themselves appropriately.

items.name: Armor of Distant Sands
items.item_description: To hide in the burning bright sun is no easy task.  It requires planning, luck, and the right color armor.

items.name: Shuriken of Distant Sands
items.item_description: Those who worship the Solar Goddess of the eastern wastes are known for the skill forging gold.

items.name: Long Blade of Distant Sands
items.item_description: The artisans of the eastern wastes are known for their ability to wrap golden beauty within sharpened practicality.

items.name: Short Blade of Distant Sands
items.item_description: Few assassins would dare use with such a finely wrought implement in combat, yet to the skilled this blade offers balance and sharpness more than equal to any task.

items.name: Featherfall Quiver
items.item_description: Made of finest rumble-hide, this low-hanging quiver of feathery arrows is ready for action!

items.name: Featherfall Spaulders
items.item_description: Designed to camouflage her outline and confuse attackers, these shoulders of tough harpy feathers offer protection against whirling blades.  This is sure to turn some heads.

items.name: Featherfall Locks
items.item_description: Hair tied up and out of the way, she tops it off with a feathery headscarf for a breezy, carefree, I-just-shot-you-in-the-face look.

items.name: Featherfall Cloak
items.item_description: A breezy, flowing cloak is just what one needs to look good on a hunting trip.  Particularly if your prey might be hunting you right back.

items.name: Featherfall Bow
items.item_description: A colorful bow adorned with tough harpy feathers is just what a feisty girl like windrunner needs for fabulous mega-kills!

items.name: Cloak of Inscrutable Zeal
items.item_description: To have a hope of examining the darkened wilds undetected requires clothing fit for sublety.

items.name: Mask of Inscrutable Zeal
items.item_description: While not as sturdy as a proper dueling mask, this covering is better tuned to project words of power.

items.name: The Oculus Ephemeral
items.item_description: Channeling the arcane and odd, the fearsome and strange, often requires implements both unexpected and unwieldy.

items.name: Staff of Inscrutable Zeal
items.item_description: The coil along the staff allows the caster to embellish the course of whatever energies it may release.

items.name: Horns of Twisted Wisdom
items.item_description: Twisted is the mind that broods beneath these twisted horns. Twisted are the intentions that issue from that mind. Twisted is the fate of those who encounter Leshrac.

items.name: Tail of Twisted Wisdom
items.item_description: Rumors have it that Leshrac once lost his tail, and after much searching and despair, an artificial appendage was attached. Perhaps this was the source of his bleak brand of wisdom.

items.name: Armor of Twisted Wisdom
items.item_description: Some insights are so painful that they burst out from within, piercing flesh, filling body and mind alike with agonizing insight.

items.name: Vines of Twisted Wisdom
items.item_description: They say that wisdom grows not without bright light, fresh air, clean water. But a twisted sort of wisdom, like these vines, may feed and thrive on anguish, black thoughts, and foul deeds.

items.name: Helmet of Omexe
items.item_description: When is a helmet both weapon and armor?  When it rests on the mighty head of Bradwarden.  Also, when it has spikes.

items.name: Armor of Omexe
items.item_description: This armor weighs more than you do.  Behold, and marvel at the strength of Bradwarden.

items.name: Bracers Omexe
items.item_description: The mighty centaur needs no shield when protected by these durable bracers of Omexe.

items.name: Flail of Omexe
items.item_description: Many lives has this mighty flail ended.  Many skulls has this mighty flail pulped.

items.name: Belt of Omexe
items.item_description: Some ask, why does a centaur need a belt?  Those people usually die.  Badly.

items.name: Tail of Omexe
items.item_description: With a playful flick of his mighty tail, a centaur registers approval.  With his flail, disapproval.

items.name: Spine of Omexe
items.item_description: Forged from the melted shields of a dozen fallen gladiators, this armor has the centaur's back.

items.name: The Dead Winter Mantle
items.item_description: His ascension to a new throne and reign of ice deserved fitting attire - Ethreain reclaimed his tattered cloak from the previous life and imbued it with a darkened frost-bound undead aura.

items.name: The Dead Winter Soul
items.item_description: Over time, the frost magic had birthed a powerful force within Ethreain. It began to florish and bloom, eventually maturing enough to manifest physically in the form of a dense crystal in his back. It continues to grow steadily and appears to reach, seeking to embrace the mage himself.

items.name: The Dead Winter Sash
items.item_description: Mastery of certain magics come with a price. As Ethreain honed his skill and grew stronger he encased his legs in ice and gathered shards to shield him. His sash helps to balance the frost within so that it does not consume him.

items.name: The Dead Winter Grasp
items.item_description: After years of the frost stirring deep inside him it began to creep out, seeking to claim him as if it had a life of its own. Enchanted cloth on his arms are a last line of defense against the icy claws reaching towards Ethreain by the dangerous, otherworldly power within.

items.name: Ancestors' Edge
items.item_description: In the founding days of the village of Pole, little but this lance stood between the simple settlers and the nightly terrors that sought to usurp them.

items.name: Ancestors' Pauldron
items.item_description: To the villagers of Pole, all must honor the creatures that surrender their lives as sustenance.

items.name: Ancestors' Vambrace
items.item_description: The cuff is adorned with Wildwing feathers.

items.name: Ancestors' Belt
items.item_description: Among the people of the village of Pole, seeing such ceremonial garb is cause for both celebration and remembrance.

items.name: Sanguine Moon Armor
items.item_description: An eye for an eye makes leaves all the heroes blind.  Except for Lycan, because he's darn sure not going to lose his second eye.  You can be sure of that.

items.name: Sanguine Moon Shoulder
items.item_description: For some heroes, a shoulder isn't a deadly weapon capable of eviscerating enemies.  Lycan isn't one of those heroes.

items.name: Sanguine Moon Weapons
items.item_description: Even his arms are armed.

items.name: Sanguine Moon Belt
items.item_description: Some have questioned the fashion sense of using a skull for a belt buckle.  The last guy who questioned it became a second belt buckle.

items.name: Sanguine Moon Patch
items.item_description: That's not an eye-patch.  That's armor for his vision.

items.name: Empowered Barding of the Gods
items.item_description: What is a warhorse without a little pomp and barding?  These golden coverings are a mark of distinction on any field of battle.

items.name: Empowered Staff of the Gods
items.item_description: With this radiant staff Keeper of the Light has sparked the heat of endless suns.

items.name: Empowered Skirt of the Gods
items.item_description: White as the light of the hottest supernova, and gold as any royal coin, this is a vestment truly worthy of a Fundamental.

items.name: Roehrin the Pale Stallion
items.item_description: On a pale horse he rides, this spark of endless suns, this Keeper of the Light.

items.name: Empowered Hood of the Gods
items.item_description: A hood to cover a wizened head and keep dark thoughts away.

items.name: Heavy Belt of the World Runner
items.item_name: Heavy Belt of the World Runner
items.item_description: If our world is but a shadow of Barathrum's real world, then this belt may be but a shadow of Spirit Breaker's real belt. But oh what a shadow!

items.name: Heavy Gauntlets of the World Runner
items.item_name: Heavy Gauntlets of the World Runner
items.item_description: When prying wide the rifts between the planes, Spirit Breaker draws power from these mighty gauntlets.

items.name: Heavy Helm of the World Runner
items.item_name: Heavy Helm of the World Runner
items.item_description: Barathrum's mighty head is his battering ram. Protect it well with this heavy helm!

items.name: Heavy Pauldrons of the World Runner
items.item_name: Heavy Pauldrons of the World Runner
items.item_description: A strange friction is generated on the physical forms of those who slide between the worlds, deeply scarring and cutting into their form. These pauldrons guard Spirit Breaker from the worst of the damage.

items.name: The Vindicator
items.item_description: To wrong Axe is dangerous.  To suffer his vindication is deadly.

items.name: Blade of the Subtle Demon
items.item_description: One must use care in the handling of such a blade, for it will cut the wielder as well as surely as the rival.

items.name: Blade of the Subtle Demon - Off-Hand
items.item_name: Blade of the Subtle Demon - Off-Hand
items.item_description: One must use care in the handling of such a blade, for it will cut the wielder as well as surely as the rival.

items.name: Veil of the Subtle Demon
items.item_description: Never reveal one's face to a foe.  Keep them ever in doubt of one's identity.

items.name: Wraps of the Subtle Demon
items.item_description: Be ever in the shadows, and wrap one's self in silence.

items.name: Whip of the Subtle Demon
items.item_description: To ensure an advantage, one must be capable of fighting from any angle.

items.name: Mark of the Subtle Demon
items.item_description: One must not balk at death.  One must learn to face all trials.

items.name: Ormr the Lunar Dragon
items.item_description: From a race of dragons that normally patrols the dark side of the moon, Ormr wanted to see the world.

items.name: Spottin' Goggles
items.item_description: Able to see a tic on a mouse's back at a thousand paces, Sniper's Spottin' Goggles are a marvel to behold.

items.name: Fishy Frillhawk
items.item_description: In Dark Reef Prison, Slark kept too low a profile to ever be called a trendsetter. He figured nobody noticed his radical look. But as soon as he had broken out, the remaining inmates began to imitate this finny style.

items.name: Scepter of the Grand Magus
items.item_description: Few know that Rubick's talents for mimicry extend to arcane assembly.

items.name: Battle Banner of the Masked
items.item_description: What good is a battle without a banner to celebrate it?  No good at all, or so says the Juggernaut.

items.name: Ancestral Bracers of Karroch
items.item_description: Worn in remembrance of his time in the stocks.  These bracers are both a symbol of his bondage, and a promise that he will never again serve nobility.

items.name: Ancestral Axes of Karroch
items.item_description: Even his axes are trained.

items.name: Ancestral Belt of Karroch
items.item_description: Woven from the pelt of a fallen pantheran, this belt is s symbol of the Beastmaster's strength.

items.name: Ancestral Hair of Karroch
items.item_description: With his head shaved to better commune with the minds of his animal brothers, Beastmaster is prepared for any battle.

items.name: Ancestral Vest of Karroch
items.item_description: A thick, protective vest of finest pantheran hide.

items.name: Battlejug of the the Drunken Warlord
items.item_name: Battlejug of the the Drunken Warlord
items.item_description: Drink from this jug and you will experience enlightenment.  Or forget why you were striving for it.

items.name: Wraps of the Drunken Warlord
items.item_description: The ancient order of the Oyo binds the sword arm of each young apprentice as a symbol of commitment to their forebears.

items.name: Guard of the Drunken Warlord
items.item_description: Designed from the cast-off remnants of ancient brew casks, these bits of aged wood have been infused with the essence of the ancient order of the Oyo.

items.name: Mailed Skirt of the Drunken Warlord
items.item_name: Mailed Skirt of the Drunken Warlord
items.item_description: When you're in your cups, this mailed skirt has your back.

items.name: Words of the Drunken Warlord
items.item_description: Did I say word?  I meant sword.  Sword of the Drunken Warlord.  There are words on it.

items.name: Bindings of Eldritch Ice
items.item_description: They sank Ethrain into the Black Pool with a weighted belt; but gravity has no pull on the Lich in his resurrected form. He wears the belt now as a mockery. And they say that all the warmth of his former heart resides in that pulsing flask, where he can keep a cold eye on it.

items.name: Glacier of Eldritch Ice
items.item_description: Drowned but not dead, deep in the Black Pool, the cold hatred in Lich's heart froze the water around him. These ice-shards, formed of evil, hold a hatred that will never melt.

items.name: Mantle of Eldritch Ice
items.item_description: The ice mage's robes became the Lich's tattered shroud. Superstitious subjects hammered spikes of sacred metal as a warning into the dead mage's skull, none suspecting that upon his resurrection he would wear the device as a cursed crown of domination.

items.name: Bracers of Eldritch Ice
items.item_description: The charmed ropes that once bound him should have rotted away, but Lich has preserved them as reminder to all that no power in creation can hope to hold him.

items.name: Blade of the Ephemeral Haunt
items.item_description: A weapon shimmering with the violent energy from Spectre's home plane of existence.

items.name: Wings of the Ephemeral Haunt
items.item_description: Energy from Spectre's home plane of existence pulses through her wings, nearly overtaking her physical form.

items.name: Sleeves of the Ephemeral Haunt
items.item_description: A billowing sleeve for Spectre, charged with the excess energy that overflows from Spectre's present form.

items.name: Horns of the Ephemeral Haunt
items.item_description: Chaotic emanations from a plane of violent power are conducted through these focal-horns and imbue Spectre with energy.

items.name: Dress of the Ephemeral Haunt
items.item_description: A dress, slightly tattered by the constant flux of spectral energy.

items.name: Akakiryu of a Thousand Faces
items.item_description: Named after a legendary dragon, this sword was given to the Juggernaut on the day he became a swordmaster.

items.name: Eye of Omoz
items.item_description: In the burning pits of the stygian waste, the sword sees all.

items.name: Sacred Bones Chopper
items.item_description: The bones of the earth that make the blade of this dagger are no less sacred than the warrior who once held it.

items.name: Sacred Bones Shoulder
items.item_description: The bones of those who came before are brought to the field of battle once more.

items.name: Sacred Bones Bracers
items.item_description: The runes upon the cuffs confer strength and courage upon the wearer.

items.name: Sacred Bones Helmet
items.item_description: The warriors of the Dezun Order hold dear the bones of those whose sacrifice has come before.

items.name: Sacred Bones Spear
items.item_description: The spear of a warrior remembers the chaos of many battles, and the taste of many lives.

items.name: Bandana of the Bone Ruin Bandits
items.item_name: Bandana of the Bone Ruin Bandits
items.item_description: Once in a while you find bandits living in the ruins.  Once in a while they forget things while they're being evicted.

items.name: Key to the Bone Ruins
items.item_description: It used to open some ancient triumphal arch, but the structure was damaged during excavation.  Using explosives probably didn't help.

items.name: Bone Ruin Excavator Pack
items.item_description: A backpack, a cloak, the finest blanket you can steal, and a little souvenir for a discerning ruffian.

items.name: Skull of the Bone Ruins
items.item_description: Even skulls get lonely up in the ruins.

items.name: The Widowmaker
items.item_description: This new item has no description.

items.name: Belt of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: A ceremonial belt of leather and brass meant to signify the high status of the wearer.

items.name: Bracers of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: Braced for combat.

items.name: Death Mask of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_name: Death Mask of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: Wear this mask, and it will be the last face your enemies ever see.

items.name: Brutal Crescent of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_name: Brutal Crescent of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: With this silver crescent, the centaur has cut the strings of many lives.

items.name: Braided Tail of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_name: Braided Tail of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: A braid woven into the tail of a centaur signifies that battle is soon at hand.

items.name: Sea Dragon's Basher
items.item_description: For sport, the Slithereen hunt the great Sea Dragons of the ocean abyss. This basher is fashioned from the spoils of one such hunt.

items.name: Sea Dragon's Crown
items.item_description: Only those who prove themselves in hunt against the great Sea Dragon dare wear such a crown.

items.name: Sea Dragon's Armlet
items.item_description: The scaly hide of the Sea Dragon is one of the few substances tougher than Slardar's own integument.

items.name: Sea Dragon's Fins
items.item_description: What appear as fins on Slardar are but the edge of the mighty Sea Dragon's tiniest gill-guards.

items.name: Spiked Pauldrons of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_name: Spiked Pauldrons of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: Made from the leather of a full grown thunderhide, this armor is a match for any blade.

items.name: Barding of the Conquering Tyrant
items.item_description: No saddle has ever graced the back of this conquering hero, but instead a barding worthy of his greatness.

items.name: Armguard of the Steppe
items.item_description: In parade to and from the arena of Omexe, no other fighter dares ride close to the Warrunner.

items.name: Sigil of the Steppe
items.item_description: No centaur shall ever wear a saddle, but a caparison such as this one is looked upon with high regard--provided one has earned it.

items.name: Plate of the Steppe
items.item_description: Not the fabled plate of Omexe, but the next best thing.

items.name: Penumbral Warblade
items.item_description: At the edge of darkness, her warblade shimmers like a piece of dusk cut loose.

items.name: Penumbral Shawl
items.item_description: Even creatures of the twilight can scarcely see the wearer of this shawl.

items.name: Penumbral Hood
items.item_description: The assassin's face is hidden, yet you can still feel through the shadows the power of her gaze.

items.name: Penumbral Crest
items.item_description: Emblazoned with the Crepuscular Sigil, this crest draws darkness over its wearer.

items.name: Penumbral Cloak
items.item_description: A cloak no less concealing than the night's long shadows.

items.name: Pauldrons of the Battle Caster
items.item_description: Once a field filled with swords and storms, Lina left little but a smoking crater and handful of grateful allies.

items.name: Vambraces of the Battle Caster
items.item_description: As the drums of war boomed on the horizon, Lina prepared to join the fray.

items.name: Plates of the Battle Caster
items.item_description: Many experiments were required, and challenges overcome, to craft material able weather Lina's flame.

items.name: Cut of the Battle Caster
items.item_description: War is said to be a cause for great innovation and invention.  No less so for fashion.

items.name: Stinger of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_description: No death has ever been more painful than that perfected by the Ancient Sovereign.

items.name: Sandworn Visage of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_name: Sandworn Visage of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_description: Unearthed from the sand-scoured ruins of El'Harath, from this Visage the entire culture of the Sovereign has been resurrected.

items.name: Claw of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_description: In the fragmentary legends of the Ancient Sovereign, death by such claws was something greatly to be desired.

items.name: Crawlers of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_description: Sandking pays tribute to the Ancient Sovereign with every step.

items.name: Vestigial Wings of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_name: Vestigial Wings of the Ancient Sovereign
items.item_description: The ancients glided stealthily above the sands in ages when these wings were not yet vestigial.

items.name: Young Alchemist's Protection
items.item_description: When you're just starting out, your formulas are a little braver, a little less precise.  And a lot more dangerous.

items.name: Young Alchemist's Knot
items.item_description: Ah, to be young again.  This haircut should help!

items.name: Ogre's Caustic Steel Bracers
items.item_description: If you're gonna work with unstable materials, make sure you can survive a mistake!

items.name: Ogre's Caustic Steel Blinders
items.item_description: What it may lack for vision it makes up for in protection.

items.name: Ogre's Caustic Steel Choppers
items.item_description: Good for stirring mixtures, great for chopping dinner!

items.name: Bracers of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: The moon shines with mystic lustre on Mirana's forearms...or is it the glow of these polished bracers?

items.name: Bow of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: The power of the lunar lioness purrs  in this bow's enchanted string.

items.name: Fluted Guard of the Moon Rider
items.item_name: Fluted Guard of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: An emblem of honor, worn with grace but never lightly.

items.name: Lion Drape of the Moon Rider
items.item_name: Lion Drape of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: The Lion of the Moon cloaks its riders in magic and might.

items.name: Andalmere the Litigon
items.item_description: Blessed by Selemene, honored among the denizens of the Nightsilver Woods, the sacred litigon Andalmere now rides to war.

items.name: Tail of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: A braid with mystic stylings woven into it.

items.name: Lion Quiver of the Moon Rider
items.item_name: Lion Quiver of the Moon Rider
items.item_description: The Lion of the Moon lends is mane and its mein to this quiver.

items.name: Staff of Wind and Sand
items.item_description: As wind and sand can wear down a mountain, so too this magical staff can wear down even the greatest foe.

items.name: The 22 Keys of Anzar-Anzuli'i
items.item_description: Of these 22 keys, one is the key to the final plane of existence.

items.name: Bridle of the Fundamental
items.item_description: A bridle of unbridled power!

items.name: Tinek the Unmastered
